title: company brisket
directions: Pour all ingredients over meat.
Use a large enameled roaster if possible.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.
Remove the foil and bake an additional 35 to 40 minutes.
Baste meat during cooking time.
Remove meat from sauce.
Cook all of the drippings until thick.
Slice on the grain thinly for sandwich buns.
Put meat back into sauce and bake for an additional 30 minutes at 350°.
Watch so sauce does not burn.
Serve on buns.

title: seasoning mix
directions: Put in bottle or jar.
Cover and shake to mix.
Store in salt shaker.

title: party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients but pretzels and nuts.
Add these at 15-minute intervals.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 or 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cream frosting
directions: Blend cocoa and butter in small bowl.
Gradually add 10x sugar alternately with milk and vanilla, beating until smooth.
Makes enough to frost 2 cake layers (8-inch).

title: hershey's cocoa fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball stage (235°) the sugar, cocoa and milk. Cool in ice water while adding margarine and vanilla.
Remove from ice water and beat candy until it starts to thicken.
Add nuts just before pouring into buttered pan.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, Karo syrup and water in saucepan; bring to a rolling boil.
While this mixture is boiling, beat egg whites until stiff. Syrup mixture will be done when a small amount dropped into a cup of cold water forms a firm ball.
When done, pour slowly into beaten egg whites, stirring constantly.
Add nuts and vanilla until mixture begins to get firm, then drop by spoonful onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Beat yolks and sugars together.
Add butter and cream.
(Can use mixer.)
Add soda to buttermilk; mix into sugar mixture.
Add raisins, jam, mincemeat and preserves; mix well.
Put cinnamon, cocoa, cloves and nutmeg into flour.
Mix all these together; add nuts.
Beat egg whites and fold in last.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in salted water. Drain dry. Add milk, sugar, eggs, salt cardamon seed and butter.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle cinnamon over the top. Bake at 400° until firm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, bell peppers and jalapenos. Drain beef.
Add refried beans.
When beans are smooth, add to Hamburger Helper cooked according to directions.
When Helper is completed, mix in corn, salsa and sour cream.
Add corn chips on top to garnish with dab of sour cream and salsa.
Ready to serve.

title: duncan hines spice cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool about 1 minute on cookie sheet.

title: stroganoff for a crowd
directions: Mix flour and salt. Sprinkle meat that has been cut into bite size strips with flour mixture.
Melt butter.
Add onions and garlic. Cook until tender, but not brown. Remove from skillet and brown meat well.

title: cajun cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease 11 x 17-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sprite salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and Sprite.
Add fruit.
Fold in Dream Whip. (May use Cool Whip instead.)
Chill and serve.

title: lake eufaula punch
directions: Dissolve lemon juice and honey.
Add gin. Put in crock and let stand overnight.
(Leave lemon rinds in mixture.) Next morning squeeze rinds and strain.
Makes about 1/5 and a half.
Serve in old fashion glasses over shaved ice.

title: zucchini salad
directions: Do not peel zucchini; shred.
Peel turnip and shred.
Chop onions, pepper and celery.
Put vegetables in a bowl.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil and salt.
Mix well and pour over vegetables. Cover and chill for 1 hour or as long as 2 days.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: biscuit pizza bake
directions: In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink.
Meanwhile, quarter the biscuits; place in a 3 quart greased, shallow baking dish.
Top with the pizza sauce.
Drain beef; sprinkle over biscuits and sauce.
Layer with green peppers, onion, mushrooms, pepperoni and cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Spread the mayo between each layer.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top layer.

title: queen bee candy
directions: Thoroughly mix together all ingredients.
Pat into a plastic lined 8 x 8 x 12 inch pan.
Cover and chill.
Cut into small squares to serve ecstasy.

title: ms. lee's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening together.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Cream each time you put the eggs in.
Add flour a little at a time, then add flavoring.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour.
Do not open oven during this time.

title: banana snowballs
directions: Cut bananas in 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Roll in lemon juice to prevent turning dark.
Soften cream cheese in microwave oven. Blend in the powdered sugar.
Coat banana pieces with cream cheese mixture.
Roll in coconut.

title: hankie-pankies
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger and drain.
Cube Velveeta and mix with hamburger and sausage until melted.
Add spices.
Mix well and spread on cocktail rye slices.
Place under broiler until bread is toasted.
Serve warm.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Place onion, mustard, salt, sugar and vinegar in blender. Blend until smooth.
Slowly add oil while blender is still running.
Fold in poppy seed after dressing is made.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Blend 1/3 cup melted butter with the chocolate wafers and pat into a 9-inch pie pan.
Chill.
In a double boiler, melt marshmallows and milk.
Melt slowly, stirring often.
Cool to room temperature.
Whip the cream and fold into marshmallow mixture. Add liqueurs.
Pour into chocolate crust and freeze.

title: non-alcoholic fruit punch
directions: Mix the ingredients and garnish with 6 oranges, 3 lemons and 3 limes, sliced; also sliced strawberries.
Serves 100.

title: tempura batter
directions: Measure flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a bowl.
Add beaten eggs and water.
When adding water, start off by adding 2 1/2 cups water.
If the batter is too thick, add more water.

title: low-cholesterol pound cake
directions: Coat bottom of loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inches) with vegetable cooking spray.
Dust with flour and set aside.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Spread over layers.
Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: italian custard
directions: Mix together sugar and oil.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix in salt and vanilla.
Sift flour and add 1 cup at a time.
Beat well.
Spread 3/4 of batter onto a greased cookie sheet.
Cover with pie filling.
Dribble remaining batter over pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Mix sugars and oleo in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add oil, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Mix flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt in small bowl.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add oats, cereal, coconut and pecans; mix well.
Drop by round teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add milk until very moist.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin and nut bars
directions: Cream egg, sugar, oleo and vanilla.
Add water (drain water from cooked raisins; cool).
Sift and add flour, cinnamon and soda.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: soy chicken wings
directions: Cut wing into 3 parts.
Discard tips.
Sprinkle wings with garlic powder and pepper.
Stir-fry in oil until almost done.
Add soy sauce and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a casserole dish, then add rice.
Mix in onion soup mix, then add 2 cups water.
Mix well.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chuck wagon steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Rub or pound into both sides of meat.
Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Brown meat on both sides. Blend beef broth, water, barbecue sauce and chili powder; pour over meat.
Cover.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add green pepper and olives. Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours longer.
Skim fat.
Thicken gravy.

title: french onion pork chops
directions: Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Spread rice over bottom.
Add water, then add 1 1/2 cans of soup.
Salt and pepper pork chops and put on top.
Add rest of soup.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Beat together the sugar, oil and eggs.
After beating, stir in the pumpkin.
Add flour mixture and batter mixture together.
Beat well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Prick and bake pie shell for 10 minutes at 450°.
Set aside. Combine chocolate pudding, egg yolks, 1/4 cup sugar and milk. Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring occasionally. Pour pudding mixture in pie shell.
Beat egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar until stiff.
Spread beaten egg whites over pudding mixture and bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until light yellow.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Sift together next 4 ingredients.
Add to first ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts or raisins.
Bake in tube pan or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: english toffee cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine crumbs, almonds, sugar and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan. In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Stir in toffee pieces.

Pour into prepared pan. Bake 50 minutes or until center is set. Turn oven off; remove from oven. Run a knife tip around edge of pan. Return to oven and let cool in oven with oven door slightly open. Chill thoroughly. Remove side of spring-form pan. Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes one 9-inch cheesecake.

title: english muffins
directions: Combine in mixing bowl:
1 cup water, sugar, milk and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Beat 2 cups flour gradually into the mixture.
Cover the bowl with a cloth and let the dough rise in a warm place (about 85°) for about 1 1/2 hours or until it collapses back into the bowl.
Beat in butter.
Beat or knead in the remaining flour.
Grease the inside of the muffin rings and fill 1/2 full with the batter.
Let them stand on a lightly greased cookie sheet until the dough has doubled in bulk (it should now fill the muffin ring).

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in the deep casserole dish which you will use for baking the cobbler.
Set aside.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef; spoon off fat.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Simmer approximately 30 minutes.
Cook noodles; rinse and combine remaining ingredients in bowl except Mozzarella cheese.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella, then meat sauce.
Repeat. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: lite cherry dessert
directions: Press graham cracker crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Mix Cool Whip with prepared pudding mix.
Pour over crumbs.
Cover with crumbs.
Put cherry pie filling on top.
Pie filling can be sweetened with Equal.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water.
Cool, remove from bone and cut into bite-size pieces.
In large casserole dish, put layer of chicken and layer of mixture of asparagus, soup, pimiento and almonds.
Repeat.
Bake in 350° oven, 30 minutes.
Sprinkle onions on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: homemade butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in margarine until golden brown; cool.
Mix rest of ingredients in blender, then add pecan mixture.
Place in ice cream freezer, then freeze according to manufacturer's directions.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased bread pan. Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.
For a variety, add 2 tablespoons onion soup mix or 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: *Sausage, bacon, ham or pepperoni.

title: cush
directions: Heat greases; add bread, seasonings and eggs.
Stir and brown lightly on stove.
Add milk to make a mushy batter.
Cook until fairly dry.
A little sugar may be added if desired.

title: seashell pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together all ingredients until well mixed. Cover; refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Makes 10 cup salad.

title: cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
In large mixing bowl, mix water, biscuit mix, mustard and 1 cup cheese.
Pour batter into pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of remaining cheese and dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes on rack before slicing.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cut up sausage, chicken, carrots, celery, green pepper, garlic, onion and fry in oil (don't fry green onions or parsley).
You may have to do one at a time.
Once fried, put in big casserole dish. (Don't do the shrimp yet.)
Add the broth, rice and tomato paste and mix well.
Bake at about 350° for about 40 minutes.
The broth will be absorbed when done.
If too dry, add some water.
Take it out of the oven and add cayenne pepper, pepper and salt.
Add recently fried shrimp.
Cook 10 more minutes.
It's done.
Add the uncooked, cut up green onions and parsley.

title: ohio buckeyes
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Make into balls the size of buckeyes.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put in casserole.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
This may be made ahead, adding onion rings just before putting in oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: deep dish turkey pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan, melt margarine; stir in flour, bouillon and pepper.
Over medium heat, gradually add milk; cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients except biscuit mix; mix well.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Prepare biscuit mix according to package directions for rolled biscuits.
Roll out to cover dish; cut slashes in center of dough.
Place on top of dish; crimp edges.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: california style brussels sprouts
directions: Steam the sprouts until they are barely cooked through and still very crisp.
Drain and dry out over the heat for a moment. Meantime, saute the garlic in the olive oil until just wilted. Add the sprouts and shake the pan well.
Add the lemon juice and pepper and shake again.
Spoon into a heated serving dish and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serve at once.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Cook chicken breasts and sausage until well done, then add cabbage.
Let come to a boil, then turn down to low and let steam 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground meat.
Light salt and pepper.
Finely chop onion and green pepper.
Add to ground meat.
Drain off excess fat.
Add 4 to 6 ounces of tomato sauce.
Cook for 10 minutes or so to blend flavors.
Spoon meat mixture into pie shell.

title: lemon garlic shrimp stir-fry
directions: Heat the olive oil in a wok or large skillet.
Add the bell pepper and zucchini.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add the shrimp, garlic and scallions.
Stir-fry over high heat for a few more minutes.
Add the snow peas.
Stir-fry until the shrimp begin to curl.
Add the lemon juice and zest.
Stir-fry until the shrimp turn pink.
Remove to a serving platter using a slotted spoon. Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley and chives. Serve with orzo, rice or noodles.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on until tender.
Let cool completely.
When ready to cook, peel and coarsely shred the potatoes.
Add green onions (use some of the tops for color).
Add salt, butter and sour cream, then toss very lightly.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden and crispy on the edges.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork into 1-inch cubes.
Add cold water and boil 20 minutes or until tender.
Cool and sprinkle heavily with soy sauce.
Dredge in flour or cornstarch and set aside.
Prepare onions, peppers and celery to keep cold.
Mix sugar, soy sauce, pineapple juice, vinegar, water and cornstarch.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Deep fry pork until crisp and brown, but not hard.
Remove and drain. Stir-fry onion, green pepper and celery for 1 minute in oil.
Pour sauce over pork; mix in vegetables and pineapple.
Mix thoroughly and serve hot.

title: lumpia
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Set aside.
Brown pork sausage and drain.
Set aside.
In a large fry pan, add oil and heat.
Add garlic, ginger, and pepper.
Simmer for one minute. Add onion and celery and simmer for two more minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add carrots, cook and stir for two minutes.
Add broccoli slaw, stir and simmer two more minutes.
Add cole slaw, stir and simmer one more minute.
Add both meats and stir well. Simmer one more minute.
Add soy sauce and stir.
Heat thoroughly (about 2-3 minutes). Pour into a colander and drain well. Refrigerate mixture overnight to chill.

title: venison round steak with onion gravy
directions: Remove fat from steak.
Sprinkle both sides of meat with tenderizer.
Pound flour into meat (both sides).
Use a little flour at a time.
In a covered skillet, melt 3 tablespoons of margarine and brown meat.
Put meat to side and brown onion; add margarine if needed.
Combine 2 cups water with bouillon, catsup and pepper; stir.
Pour over meat.
Turn heat low; simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally and do not let simmer dry.
Add water to keep liquid level at about 2 cups.
Mix 1/4 cup cold water with 4 tablespoons of flour; stir until smooth and add slowly to make gravy.
Stir constantly.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: frito pie
directions: Cook hamburger meat and add taco mix as directed, but more water.
Then in deep casserole dish, combine 1 layer large Fritos, 1 layer taco meat with sauce and 1 layer grated Cheddar cheese. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbles.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Beat butter, sugars, vanilla and water together until creamy. Beat in egg.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together and mix in. Spread in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 6 ounces semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 2 minutes.
Run a knife through dough to marbleize.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes more.

title: bean goulash
directions: Brown in skillet bacon, hamburger and onion.
Drain excess grease off.
Mix together catsup, brown sugar, salt, vinegar, mustard, lima, kidney and pork and beans.
Stir in meat mixture. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° in covered casserole (works well in crock-pot also).

title: low-fat cucumber or garlic dip
directions: Mix yogurt, cucumber or garlic and chives in bowl.
Blend cottage cheese and lemon juice in blender.
Add to yogurt mixture. Refrigerate several hours for flavors to blend.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix with wooden spoon, do not beat. Add 3/4 c. warm water. Mix well and pour into a 9 inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir ingredients together. Pour into pan. Sprinkle with 2 cups corn flake crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Grind cucumbers, pepper and onions.
Add tomatoes and carrots and drain.
In a double boiler pan over warm water dissolve 3 tablespoons of ground mixture.
Soak gelatin in mixture.
Add this mixture to the vegetables and fold in mayonnaise.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Spread on bread when ready to serve.

title: cherry spoon cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 3 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Line pan with cherry filling and spread pineapple over this.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Pour melted butter evenly over the mix. Sprinkle the coconut and nuts on top.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool completely before serving.
Can use other fruit filling.

title: swiss meringue
directions: Beat the egg whites until frothy.
Add the salt and cream of tartar and beat well.
Add the sugar gradually, while continuing to beat.
Add the vanilla and continue beating until the mixture is glossy and stiff, but not dry.
Cover baking sheets with waxed paper and using a spoon, shape the meringue into any desired form. Bake in a very slow oven (225°) until firm and dry, but still white, 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove the meringues from the paper while warm.
Serve at room temperature, filled with cold fruit or ice cream or frozen yogurt.
Makes 12 meringue shells.

title: crispy treats
directions: Cook
the
first
3 ingredients in saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Pour
over Rice Krispies.
Pour on cookie sheet or a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Mix
all
the
ingredients, but the tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to
taste.
Cut
a
slice from top of tomato, scoop out inside and add
this
to the mixture.
Stuff the tomatoes and place in
a baking
dish and cover bottom of dish with water. Bake at 350° until tomatoes are tender, 15 or 20 minutes.

title: bible school punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed; add lemonade and pineapple juice. Mix well.
Makes 5 to 8 quarts.

title: vickie's pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lazy man's pie
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Pour in sugar and mix well.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well again.
Sift flour and baking powder into this mixture and stir in peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Dissolve cube in boiling water. Dissolve cornstarch in soy sauce.
Spray non-stick skillet with vegetable spray.
Quickly brown chicken over high heat, stirring constantly.
Add bouillon, ginger and soy sauce mixture.
Cook until thickened over low heat, stirring to coat vegetables.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cook and drain sausage; crumble into small pieces and set aside.
Cut tops from large tomatoes and carefully scoop out insides with a small spoon, leaving the tomato shell.
Place centers and juice in a large bowl (centers may be rather firm so mash into pulp).
Roll cracker crumbs and add to tomato pulp and juice, leaving the mixture very moist.
Add pork sausage and mix well.
Fill tomato shells with mixture.
Place close together in baking pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: strawn slick-em
directions: Slice bananas in half lengthwise.
Spread a layer of mayonnaise on freshly cut flat portion of banana.
Top with your favorite nuts.

title: congo bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Let butter soften.
Add sugar.
Beat.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavoring and dry ingredients (sift together).
Add chips and nuts.
Grease pan (9 x 13-inch or 10 x 14-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Take out of pan and slice into finger bars.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt in large bowl. Add oil and eggs.
Mix.
Stir in strawberries and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans at 350°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package; drain. Place in a baking dish.
Mix the cheese, onion, mayonnaise, soup and water.
Pour this mixture over the broccoli and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nutritious poppin fresh cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup. Level off.

title: cold eggplant spread
directions: Broil eggplant in oven for 15 to 25 minutes, until it pops open.
Remove center and discard skin.
Run eggplant in blender until mushy or use fork.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Great with crackers or chips.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: grape ale
directions: Fill glasses with ice.
Pour glass half full of grape juice. Add ginger ale to fill glasses; stir.
Serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: miracle shake and bake mix
directions: Mix thoroughly dried bread crumbs with rest of ingredients. Store in jar in refrigerator.
Use as needed for chicken, pork chops, or fish.
Brush meat with melted margarine and coat with this mixture.
Bake until done.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Spread pecan halves in a baking pan.
Pour melted butter over the nuts and toss well.
Roast nuts in a moderately slow oven at 325° for about 25 minutes or until they are lightly colored and sizzling.
During roasting, shake them several times.
Sprinkle with salt and a few grinds of pepper.
Shake the pan to distribute seasonings.
Cool nuts and transfer to airtight jar and store in refrigerator.

title: 1-2-3-4 dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Add milk and stir only until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls into stew or broth.
Cover pan tightly, bring to boiling point, lower heat and steam 15 minutes.

title: presco delight sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Spread mixture on hamburger buns (makes 14 small).
Wrap sandwiches in foil.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: In a large bowl of electric mixer, prepare chocolate cake mix according to package instructions.
Pour half the batter (reserve other half) into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form loaf.
Bake, covered, in a baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes to brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9x12 baking dish.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Add milk gradually and stir well.
Pour into melted butter.
Do not stir as it will keep crust from forming.
Pour peaches and juice in mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 mins. or until done.

title: chewy raisin bars
directions: In a saucepan heat and stir brown sugar and butter or margarine until butter is melted.
Remove from the heat and cool about 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, stir together flour and baking powder.
Beat egg and vanilla into mixture in the saucepan until well mixed. Stir in flour mixture.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven about 25 minutes or until done.
Cut into bars while warm.
Cool.
Sift powdered sugar over bars before serving.
Makes 24.

title: bernie's ugly green stuff
directions: *Optional for those who must raise cholesterol level.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Cream egg and sugar; add 1/2 cup flour and mix well. Add salt and vanilla. Add soda to cherries. Hold over bowl as this foams up and turns very dark. Add remaining 1/2 cup flour; mix well. Add 1 cup nuts (not black walnuts). Bake in greased, floured pan, 9 x 13-inch or loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Serve with dip or whipped cream or both. Keeps well.

title: dump cake
directions: Melt margarine; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make sure butter covers bottom of entire pan.
Pour pineapple juice, pineapple and fruit cocktail in pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over it.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine above (except nuts and cinnamon/sugar).
Beat for 2 minutes. Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour small amount of batter into bottom of cake pan. Sprinkle cinnamon/sugar.
Pour 1/2 of remaining batter into pan.

Sprinkle cinnamon/sugar and some of the chopped nuts. Take knife and swirl mixture. Pour remaining batter and repeat cinnamon/sugar and nuts. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Cool 20 minutes and remove from pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs with both sugars, then mix all other stuff together. Last pour pecans in.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in either two 9 or 8-inch pie pans unbaked or one 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Very easy!

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Then add other baking soda, chocolate chips and sifted flour.
Mix together until thoroughly mixed.
Put 1/2 teaspoon of mix on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: Dust pork chops lightly with flour.
Dip chops into milk and egg mixture, then dredge in flour once more.
Shake off excess flour.
Fry in hot cooking oil over medium heat until lightly brown on both sides.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and salt in a pan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool until firm.
Serves 36.

title: jo's quick mess
directions: Peel and slice peaches very thin.
Add peach glaze.
Mix well. Put in casserole dish and cover with Cool Whip.
Quick, tasty dessert.
Goes extremely well with pound cake.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Slice potatoes thinly in casserole dish first.
Brown pork chops in oil.
Drain off excess oil.
Mix mushroom soup with milk well.
Place pork chops onto potatoes. Pour mushroom soup over meat and potatoes.
Cover with foil for 1/2 hour.
Remove foil and bake 1/2 hour more or until potatoes are done.
Absolutely out of this world!

title: cheese fondue
directions: Combine above and melt slowly in microwave, stirring often.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add 2 teaspoons of tea mix to hot water.
You can make one cup at a time if desired.
Sugar can also be added to taste.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop
onions,
peppers,
pimentos,
mix
all
together. Chill until firm shape in to a ball and roll in chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: brown rice
directions: Heat bacon drippings in a skillet and add onions and mushrooms.
Cook until tender; add rice and soy sauce and cook 10 minutes on low heat.
Add bacon and mix well.

title: flaky pastry mix
directions: This mix may be used as a pie, tart or baked dumpling crust.

title: confetti con queso
directions: In medium saucepan, stir together Cheez Whiz, Thick 'N Chunky salsa and 1/2 chopped bell peppers.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Transfer to serving bowl.
Sprinkle with remaining chopped bell peppers.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mushrooms in brown sauce
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute onions to golden brown in butter.
Cut mushrooms into pieces.
Place in saucepan with 1/2 cup water.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Then add to skillet with onions.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over pierogi or as a side dish.

title: date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates, soda and butter.
Let stand for about 5 minutes.
Stir until dates are in small pieces.
Beat eggs, salt and vanilla.
Add to mixture.
Add sugar gradually. Beat until thick.
Add flour and baking powder which have been sifted together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: my e-z pickles
directions: Save liquid from store bought dill pickles. Add any of the following:
beets, carrots, cauliflower, peaches or pears.
Store, covered (empty pickle jar works fine), in refrigerator.
Allow to set 2 to 3 days to blend flavors.

title: butterfly pork chops
directions: In skillet saute onion, green and red pepper (sliced) in olive oil.
Season with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Remove from skillet.
In same olive oil brown butterfly pork chops.
After browning pork chops, add onion, green pepper and red pepper.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer for at least 2 hours, covered.
Serve with angel hair spaghetti (cook as directed on package).
Sauce will be served over the spaghetti.
Delicious and easy.
Serve with green vegetables, salad and Italian bread.
Enjoy.
Thanks.

title: chanda's good good casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown bread crumbs with butter in frying pan until crispy brown.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 300° for around 45 minutes.
Bake uncovered.

title: sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage in small amount of olive oil.
Add tomatoes and water and then vegetables, barley and seasonings.

title: greek tomato salad
directions: Cut tomatoes to bite size (a basket of small ones may also be used).
Cut olives in half.
Crumble the cheese coarsely or cube. Rub bowl with garlic; add tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Sprinkle with vinegar and olive oil.
Add seasonings and toss.
Marinate for at least 4 hours.
If longer, store in refrigerator until 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Serve at room temperature.
Great with pork or lamb.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread the pie filling on top of pineapple.
Next, spread the yellow cake mix on top of pie filling.
Slice margarine and place on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: incredible chocolate mousse
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks separately, until very pale yellow.
Add yolks, salt and vanilla to cooled melted chocolate.
Fold egg whites into mixture.
Pour into souffle dish. Cover and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: red hot apple jello(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Pour boiling water over jello and mix until dissolved.
Add applesauce and red hots.
Cook over medium heat until candies are dissolved.
Pour into ring mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold onto plate and fill center with whipped cream, cottage cheese or Waldorf Salad.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Bake in 9-inch pie shell until golden brown.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Cream butter and blend in sugar.
Add eggs, lemon peel and vanilla.
Beat together until well blended. Stir flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with lemon juice. Drop by rounded teaspoons onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Frost while still warm.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: can of soup chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup, milk, onion and parsley.
Stir until well mixed.
Combine noodles with chicken mixture and place in casserole dish.
Place buttered bread cubes on top of mixture. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, until mixture is bubbly and bread cubes are browned.

title: baked caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in syrup and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda, vanilla and salt.
Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Turn into a large greased roaster or baking pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool completely.
Break apart.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: italian beef
directions: Roast meat uncovered at 350° until internal reading is 150°, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Cool and slice.
Add water and bouillon to pan drippings; stir in seasonings and green peppers.
Simmer 15 minutes (do not allow to boil).
Put sliced beef into marinade and refrigerate overnight.
Reheat to serve.
Can be frozen.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, salt, onions and garlic in ice 3 hours. Drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed and bring to a boil.
Put drained cucumbers in boiling mixture and bring to another boil; when cucumbers change color, put in jars and seal.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In bowl with mixer, combine sour cream, cream cheese and sugar.
Blend well.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip and place in slightly oiled mold and freeze.
Thaw only slightly before serving.
Very good with chicken and dressing or roast.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare instant pudding as directed on box.

When cake is cooled, crumble 1/2 of the cake in the bottom of a large punch bowl, then pour 1/2 of the pudding over the cake, then layer 1/2 of the cherry pie filling, pineapple, 3 sliced bananas and 1/2 of strawberries in that order over the pudding.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip over bananas, then begin the layers again, starting with the cake and ending with the Cool Whip.
You can garnish the top with strawberries, cherries or nuts.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients into cold water.
Freeze what you have leftover.
Very good.

title: nana's jello pound cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup water.
Cool slightly.
Add package of cake mix, oil, eggs and extract.
Beat for 5 minutes. Pour into an ungreased tube pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: my best minestrone soup ever
directions: Fry bacon just until done; do not burn.
Heat oil in large pot and saute green onions, bacon, onion, garlic, cabbage, potatoes and celery for 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except cheese; let simmer for 30 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Serve, sprinkled with the Parmesan cheese.

title: wild rice casserole(serves 8)
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet.
Remove from heat.
Drain on paper towel.
Pour off fat, reserving 3 tablespoons.
Saut mushrooms and onions in reserved fat.
Return crumbled sausage to the skillet.
Meanwhile, cook rice according to the directions on the box, but only for 15 minutes.
Drain.
In a separate pan, mix flour and heavy cream until smooth.
Add chicken broth and cook until thick.
Combine sauce, rice, sausage, mushrooms and onions. Mix well.
Add seasonings to taste.
Pour into a large buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle toasted almonds on top and serve.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix cookie crumbs with melted butter.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread ice cream over top of cookies.
Pour fudge topping in even layer over ice cream.
Spread whipped topping over fudge.
Garnish with 1/4 cup leftover cookie crumbs.
Put in freezer for two hours.

title: easy meatball bake
directions: Mix beef, onion soup mix and eggs.
Make meatballs.
Place in oblong baking dish.

title: microwave hot spinach dip
directions: Microwave cream cheese in dish for 30 seconds. Add onion, seasonings and milk to cheese and stir well. Remove outer wrapper on package of spinach and microwave for 5 minutes or until completely defrosted. Give half turn during cooking.
Drain spinach thoroughly.
Stir ham and spinach into cheese mixture. Fold in sour cream and pecans.
Microwave 5 minutes or until very hot. Stir gently after 2 minutes.
Serve warm.
Power on Microwave:
High.

title: shoo-fly pie(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and reserve 1/2 cup for crumbs.
Blend together rest of ingredients and add to first mixture.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and top with reserved crumbs.
Bake for 35 minutes in 375° oven.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese, vanilla pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Layer cookies, bananas and pudding mix and crumble cookies on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: fall apple dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients except last 2 (apples and orange juice).
Wash and slice apples.
Dip in orange juice. Drain.
Arrange in concentric circles on plate and place the dip in the center in a bowl.
Sprinkle additional chopped peanuts on top of dip.
Refrigerate.

title: leftover night
directions: Cook ground chuck, onion and bell pepper together.
Cook rice, then add beans, corn, Ro-Tel, salsa, salt, pepper and ground chuck mixture. Add jalapeno peppers.

title: garlic bread
directions: About 25 minutes before serving:
Over low heat, in a small saucepan, cook olive oil, salt and garlic for 5 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: hot cranberry cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Discard spices.
Serve warm.

title: summer pie
directions: Mix together pineapple, milk, Cool Whip, lemon juice and nuts. Pour into pie shell.
Freeze.
Don't take it out until ready to slice and serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend together in mixer:
butter, flour, sugar and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place in greased baking dish and bake at 325° for one hour.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into ball.
Roll in chopped fresh parsley and pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: saltine cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place crackers in 1 layer on cookie sheet. Pour the melted butter over all.
Place in oven and heat until mixture bubbles.
Remove from oven and pour the chocolate chips over.
Spread with a spatula.
Cool.
With knife (sharp), cut into squares.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans in
water
overnight.
In same liquid, bring beans to boil and simmer
until
tender,
about
1/2 hours.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Combine
remaining
ingredients
with beans. Put into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 4 hours, adding liquid occasionally if necessary.
Cover,
during first half of baking time, then uncover.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together and store in container.
Use 3 heaping spoonfuls in cup of boiling water.
Stir well.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until thread is spun on spoon, about 238°.
Add butter, peanuts and vanilla.
Cook until peanuts begin popping, about 290°.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and stir quickly.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet with sides.
When cold, break by hitting the candy with a metal tablespoon.
Do all stirring with a wooden spoon.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add green chilies and cook until clear, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add soup and milk; bring to boil.
Soften tortilla strips in skillet with melted butter.
In a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer tortillas, chicken soup mixture and cheese.
End with cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan patties
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and mix well.
Beat eggs and add to dry ingredients.
Put margarine in a casserole dish.
Place in oven and let margarine melt.
Form patties by hand and place in dish.
Let them bake until browned on the bottom, about 20 minutes, at 350°.
When browned, turn the patties over and pour the tomato sauce over all.
Return patties to the oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Also makes loaf.

title: date balls
directions: Melt oleo in heavy pot. Add sugar and work good.
Let cool. Add egg yolks, dates and nuts.
Mix together.
Cook over low heat 8 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Cool until can handle.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.

title: biscuit breakfast ring
directions: Melt sugar, butter and water; place 6-ounce custard glass in center of round glass dish.
Sprinkle nuts evenly around custard cup.
Cut each biscuit in half; coat each piece in sugar mixture. Arrange around custard dish.
Cook in microwave 2 1/2 to 3 minutes. Turn dish halfway through cooking, let stand 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes in conventional oven.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon on top.
Fill pan not quite to top.
Mix topping together until crumbly.
Place on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Basic marinade for meat, poultry and seafood.
Marinating times depend on thickness.
Example:
chicken thighs equal 3 to 4 hours.
Thinly sliced (1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness) beef, 2 hours. Can be used as basting sauce.

title: turkey in a bag
directions: You will need a brown grocery bag.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Spread fruit in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, Bisquick and egg.
Crumble over fruit.
Chip 1 stick of butter over cobbler.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy peas salad
directions: Combine dressings; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly and chill.
Can be served alone or in tomatoes.

title: crunchy potato chip salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise and vinegar.
Stir in cabbage, tuna, carrot, green pepper and onion.
Cover; chill. Just before serving, add potato chips; toss lightly.

title: london broil
directions: Stir together salad oil, lemon juice, garlic, salt and pepper. Brush on top side of meat.
Set oven at broil.
Broil meat 2 to 3-inches from heat about 5 minutes or until brown.
Turn meat; brush with oil mixture and broil 5 minutes longer.
(I prefer to cook outside on charcoal grill allowing more time to cook.)
Cut meat across grain at a slanted angle into thin slices.
Serves 6.

title: christmas toddy
directions: Mix red hots, cinnamon stick, whole cloves and brown sugar. Fill coffeepot (10 cup size) with water after cranberry juice and pineapple juice have been added.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Make jello using the 2 cups of water.
Add other ingredients and pour into mold.
Chill and serve.
Looks very pretty in Alpine mold.

title: mushroom meat puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup and water. Form into balls. Sprinkle with flour and brown in hot cooking oil.
Drain oil.
Mix can of soup with 1/2 cup water and pour over meat balls.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Use electric skillet for entire process.
Serve over pasta or rice.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream 2 cups sugar with 1/2 cup butter.
Add 2 eggs, beating well after each.
Sift two cups flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add to cream mixture along with 1 cup buttermilk.
Mix together, 1 cup hot water, 1/2 cup cocoa, 1 teaspoon soda.
Mix with other ingredients, and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
2 greased and floured pans, 9-inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fido's feast homemade dog bones
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, combine all, except flour.
Mix well.
Add flour, one cup at a time, mixing well after each addition to form a stiff dough.
On floured surface, knead in remaining flour until dough is smooth and no longer sticky, 3 to 4 minutes.
Roll or pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut in bone shapes or bite-size pieces.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown.
Store loosely covered.

title: royal rice
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add rice, mushrooms and salt.
Heat thoroughly.
Fluff lightly with a fork.
Makes six servings.

title: scotch short bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat in mixture.
Half dough and make two balls.
Press on cookie sheet with brown paper on it. Flattened ball should make a round circle 1/2-inch thick.
Repeat with other ball.

title: chocolate oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with 1/4 cup oleo (melted).
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Spread softened vanilla ice cream on crust and freeze.
Mix milk, sugar and chocolate.
Stir and cook until thick (25 to 30 minutes).
Add 1 tablespoon butter and vanilla and allow to cool completely.
Spoon over ice cream and return to freezer.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Oreos.
Put in freezer.
Keeps 2 weeks.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: In a medium skillet, melt butter and brown chicken.
In a bowl, blend remaining ingredients; add to skillet.
Simmer, turning occasionally, 10 minutes or until tender.
Place chicken on bed of rice.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix everything together (the chips last).
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Great served with Chocolate Whip Cream.

title: dilled vegetable salad
directions: Combine veggies. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over veggies. Toss. Chill overnight. Serve cold.

title: beef pot pie
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown meat on all sides in a small amount of fat.
Take plenty of time for browning; rich flavor and color depend on it.
Add onion, garlic, bay leaf, salt, sugar, paprika, pepper and Worcestershire.
Pour in water.
For tender meat, remember to cook at a gentle bubbling; boiling toughens meat. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Remove bay leaf and garlic.
Add the vegetables to the meat, cover and cook 30 minutes.
Add peas.
Continue cooking 10 minutes more or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Remove stew from heat and skim off fat.
To thicken stew, in a gravy shaker put 1/2 cup cold water and 1/4 cup flour, shake to blend.
With stew removed from heat, slowly stir in flour mixture.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until gravy thickens.
Cook and stir 5 minutes more.
Serve as stew or top with biscuits.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix
first
ingredients well.
Add chopped onion and Tabasco and mix well.
Stir in chopped shrimp.
This is better if prepared
ahead and kept in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: quick sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into balls the shape of walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in microwave.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Microwave 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.
Layer 1/2 of potatoes, onions and sauce in a greased casserole.
Repeat layers. Cover and microwave 17 to 19 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Mix eggs and milk together, then add to flour mixture.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in the blender. (Use 9 ice cubes for a drink, 12 for slush.) Blend on high until the ice becomes quiet. Serve at once.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix together oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour liquids over mixture of beans, onions and green peppers.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Cut rolls in half and set aside.
Mix all ingredients except ham and cheese until smooth.
Spread on lower half of rolls. Place ham and cheese slices and cover with roll tops.
Heat and serve.

title: mountain blackberry cobbler
directions: Make sure frozen blackberries are thawed and well drained. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: working girl batter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water.
Add remaining ingredients. Add milk slowly to make a sticky batter.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pan and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
This is one you don't have to let batter rise.

title: violet jam
directions: Rinse violet blossoms well; place in a blender.
Add 3/4 cup water and lime juice; blend well.
Gradually add sugar, blending until a smooth paste is formed.
In saucepan, combine pectin and remaining water; bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add to blender; blend for 1 minute.
Quickly pour into prepared jars or glasses and seal.
Be sure to use wild violets (common, not hot house African violets).

title: grits au gratin
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add salt and grits.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Take off burner.
Add Velveeta cheese in cubes.
Stir until melted.
Add margarine.
Stir until melted; cool.
Beat eggs and add when cool.
Stir in Tabasco sauce.
Pour in buttered baking dish.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: sweet potato pie with pecan topping
directions: Cook potatoes until soft. Drain and mash.
Add sugar, oleo, eggs, vanilla and enough milk to make creamy.
Bake in pie shell until almost firm.

title: chunky country-style spiced applesauce
directions: Combine apples, water and lemon juice in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes (apples should be tender).

title: dump cake
directions: Put each ingredient in order given into a 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Add 2 cups crushed cornflakes.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, melted butter and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, egg and 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzels.
Mix Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Refrigerate.
Add berries when Jell-O thickens.
Spread over cream cheese.

title: cherry topped cheese pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool and top with preserves.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas; blend well.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately, blend well.
Add nuts.
Bake one hour in 350 °oven in medium loaf pan (oiled).
Wrap tightly in foil to store.
Best if stored in refrigerator.

title: herbal vinegar
directions: You will need wide mouth jar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain and mash.
Add cheese, butter, egg, milk and crackers.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake in shallow casserole dish at 350° until set and brown (about 45 minutes).

title: kielbasa rolls
directions: Put milk, butter, sugar & salt on stove in saucepan and heat (do not boil) until butter is melted. Set aside until it is lukewarm before use. (If it is hot, it will ruin yeast). Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add to milk mixture; then add flour & mix. Set in warm place for 15 minutes, then pinch off and place sausage pieces inside. Place on greased pan for 15 minutes. Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 10-15 minutes.

title: 5 layer dinner
directions: Ground beef can either be broken up in pieces or made into patties.
Place ingredients in layers in greased 2-quart casserole. Garnish with green pepper, if desired.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: pecan pie(club member: laine)
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Prepare pastry. Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup with rotary beater. Stir in nuts. Pour into pastry-lined pie pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set. Do not overcook.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and pumpkin and water mix.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices. Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins or dates.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Lightly spray casserole.
Mix first six ingredients.
Layer in casserole and place chicken on top.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken.
Seal with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Don't peak!

title: ravioli and meat balls
directions: Lightly form chuck into 24 balls.
In hot oil in large skillet, brown meat balls about 10 minutes.
Drain off fat.

title: chocolate zucchini cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Add egg.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and zucchini. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Mix soup and milk.
Layer in baking dish the chips, beef, half of onions, half of cheese and pour half of soup mixture over all.
Repeat layering.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine ground beef, egg, onions, green peppers, pepper, salt, oats and milk.
Add 1/4 cup tomato sauce and mix thoroughly.
Press mixture into an 11 x 7-inch casserole dish. Pour remaining tomato sauce over meat loaf mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poached salmon in tomato broth
directions: Peel and seed tomatoes*. Puree the tomatoes in an electric blender or food processor. Combine the pureed tomatoes, wine or broth, butter and fennel seeds in a large skillet over moderate heat. Place salmon fillets on top and sprinkle with the chopped basil. Season with salt and pepper and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple fritters from martin's orchard
directions: Mix milk, egg, butter, sugar and salt.
Add orange juice, flour, baking powder and vanilla. Gently fold in the chopped apples.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into hot oil (350°), until golden brown, turning to brown evenly.
Drain on paper towel. Roll in powdered sugar.
Enjoy!

title: vegetable jalfarezi
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Add cumin seed, onions, beans, green pepper and carrots.
Saute for a minute or two.
Add the rest of the vegetables and saute again.
Add salt to taste, chili powder and touch of tomato sauce.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: *Can use 3/4 cup mixed candied fruits in place of cherries and orange peel.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix flour and 1/4 cup water to make paste.
In 1 1/2 quarts water, cook celery and onion until tender (20 minutes).
Add potatoes; cook until done (about 20 minutes).
Add salt, butter and milk.
Stir in water and flour mixture, stirring until smooth. Serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake(makes one 9-inch cheesecake)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs and margarine; pat firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand; beat until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
In small bowl, toss together 1/2 cup chips with flour to coat; stir into cheese mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips evenly over top.
Bake 1 hour or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill.
Remove side of pan.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Scald, peel and quarter tomatoes.
Add sugar.
Let stand overnight. Drain off juices and boil rapidly, until it spins a thread.
Add tomatoes and lemons; boil until thick and clear. Pour into sterilized jars and seal with lids as filled.

title: basic pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Grease large tube pan; sprinkle lightly with flour. Pour into tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken in beer
directions: Combine flour, salt and
pepper
in shallow dish.
Roll chicken pieces in flour,
coating
well.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook frequently, turning until chicken is
golden,
about 12 to 15 minutes. Add beer and onions.
Cover;
reduce
heat and simmer, turning occasionally,
until chicken
is
tender,
about
minutes. Blend in whipping cream
and
parsley.
Increase heat to medium-high.
Continue to cook until
heated through, about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: cheese pennies
directions: In mixer bowl, mix all ingredients on medium speed 20 to 30 seconds.
On lightly floured surface, mold dough into 2 rolls, 1-inch in diameter and about 8 inches long.
Dought will be soft but not sticky.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill at least 2 hours. Heat oven to 375°.
Cut rolls into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: cowboy caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cream cheese, eggs and onion. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, chop broccoli, pecans, onion and apple. Grate the cheeses and add.
Quarter and slice bananas; add.
In another bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and pickle juice.
Stir over other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: poppy seed lemon bread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: ham and cheese puff
directions: Combine ham, cheese, mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread on 6 slices toasted bread.
Put together remaining slices, like a sandwich.
Cut each sandwich in 4 pieces.
Arrange in a baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam or brushed with oleo.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Pour over sandwiches, leaving space between bread so milk can run in.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: jordan's ham and cheese forward rolls
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Slice through the rolls lengthwise.
Spread mixture on both sides of the rolls.
Place ham and cheese on rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Heat for 10 minutes at 400°. If made ahead and refrigerated, heat for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs (one at a time while beating), vanilla and lemon extract. Then add flour, salt, soda sifted with alternating sour cream. Grease a Bundt pan. Pour mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Cake is done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in Toll House morsels and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: bat zappers
directions: A recipe for children to make.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in a small bowl.
Great for ribs or chicken.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy; add eggs.
Combine flour and baking
powder.
Alternate
adding flour mixture and milk. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Chop 10 eggs and combine with potatoes in a large bowl. Combine milk, mustard, salt, pepper and onion in container of blender; whirl until onion is finely chopped.
Add mayonnaise and vinegar and whirl just to blend.
Pour over egg-potato mixture and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
When ready to serve, slice remaining eggs; sprinkle salad with parsley.
Garnish with egg slices.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: quick and easy quiche
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add half and half and rest of ingredients. Pour into 9-inch pastry-lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box.
Bake in three 8 1/2-inch pans as directed.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour 1/2 the batter into a greased casserole.
Cover entire surface with chiles.
Sprinkle on a generous amount of grated cheese.
Pour rest of batter on top of chili-cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: three month pickles
directions: Cover and let set 3 months; shake everyday.
Wash and drain. Add 4 cups sugar; let set 1 week.
Ready to eat.

title: onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter slowly.
Remove and drain.
Put in pie shell.
Combine cheese, flour, salt and cayenne.
Stir in beaten eggs and milk.
Pour over onions and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: my potato soup
directions: Place all ingredients in medium sized pot (heavy to keep from scorching).
Simmer over low to medium heat, stirring occasionally until potatoes are done.
Grated cheese may be added to top after cooked.

title: tamale pie for 12
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 250°.

title: noodle nibble
directions: Combine butter, soy sauce and Tabasco.
Drizzle over noodles; toss until well coated.
Sprinkle with celery salt and onion powder, tossing to mix.
Toast in slow oven at 275° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes with apple
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan with 1 teaspoon of margarine.
Lay the sweet potatoes and apple slices in the pan in a circle, alternating and overlapping the slices.

title: zucchini dressing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in salted water for 5 minutes; drain. Brown sausage and drain.
Combine sour cream, soup, zucchini and carrots.
Add margarine to dressing.
Layer 1/2 of dressing in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour vegetables over and sprinkle sausage on.
Add remaining dressing and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with 1 cup grated cheese; return to oven to melt.

title: bran flake muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over bran flakes and let stand 3 minutes; set aside.
In separate bowl, combine shortening, sugar and eggs; set aside.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Now, combine all ingredients with buttermilk.
Bake in greased muffin pan in a preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen. Batter may be kept in refrigerator up to 4 weeks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: golden ripe banana doughnut
directions: Mash peeled bananas into a bowl, using a potato masher or a fork.
Add flour and mix.
Add sugar and mix well.
Put oil in pan and heat (deep fat frying).
When oil is hot, drop mixture by spoonfuls into oil, turning frequently.
Cook until golden brown on both sides.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap ball in waxed paper and chill.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick foil or with regular foil coated with nonstick spray. In large microwave-safe bowl, melt together butter and chocolate in microwave oven on HIGH for 2 minutes; stir until smooth. Whisk in eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla. Stir in pecans. Spread half the batter into prepared pan. Sprinkle with 1 cup chocolate chunks. In medium-size saucepan, melt together caramels and heavy cream over medium-low heat until smooth, about 5 minutes. Evenly pour over batter in pan. Spread with remaining batter. Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup chocolate chunks. Bake in 350° oven until top is dry to the touch, about 35 minutes. Let cool completely in pan on wire rack. Lift brownie from pan with foil. Cut into squares.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top of hot cake and cover with your favorite chocolate frosting!

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles. Layer noodles, Ragu sauce and cheese in 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 325° or until hot.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans, bring to boil and let soak 1 hour; drain.
Add new water.
Season with garlic salt, seasonings and hot sauce.
Add onion.
Cook on medium all day.
Add water when needed.
About 1 hour before serving, add sausage.
Serve over rice, with cornbread.

title: fruit salad ice(30 servings)
directions: Drain apricots and pineapple; reserve liquid and add water to make 1 cup liquid.	Heat liquid and sugar until sugar dissolves. Add strawberries and their juice, orange juice and lemon juice. Cut up apricots and bananas; add to mixture along with pineapple. Spoon into cupcake papers placed in muffin tins.
Freeze until solid.
Remove from tins and store in plastic bags.
Remove from freezer 10 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and green pepper.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: novaks chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in pan.
After mixture comes to boil (1 1/2 minutes), remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until creamy. Add oatmeal and stir.
Spoon on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: tamale-bean bake
directions: Place tamales in baking dish.
Top with beans, onion and cheese.
Pour tomato sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: chocolate mocha cake
directions: Put dry ingredients into a large bowl, then add eggs, oil and cold water.
Stir to mix well, then gradually add boiling water. Mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or two (8-inch) pans for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Thaw rolls.
Mix dry pudding mix, sugar and cinnamon together. Sprinkle 1/2 nuts on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put rolls on top of nuts. Sprinkle sugar and pudding mixture over rolls. Drizzle butter on top. Cover with greased wax paper and towel overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert pan on platter or foil covered cookie sheet to serve.

title: pork chops with pears, blue cheese and green peppercorns
directions: Note:
To crush peppercorns, press them with the flat side of a knife blade.

title: kraut
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook on low heat for 1 1/2 hours or you can cook on higher heat for a shorter amount of time. Saute chopped onion in butter until soft; mix with the kraut and serve.

title: speonk goulash
directions: Put carrots, potatoes and onions in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Top with sausage.
Mix sauce and water together.
Pour over casserole.
Bake one hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pull chicken off bone and place in a 11 x 14-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup together and spread over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix, broth, eggs and onion and spread over soup.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: garlic chicken
directions: In a Ziploc bag, put chicken pieces and a liberal amount of soy sauce and garlic powder.
Close bag tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Remove chicken and grill over charcoals or broil. Baste with soy sauce and garlic mixture.
Grill or broil about 15 to 20 minutes per side.

title: mary lou's coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Thoroughly mix mayonnaise, milk, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mixture should be tart.
Pour over cabbage and mix well.
Add pineapple to mixture.
Let stand at least an hour before serving.
Mix well before serving.

title: tom prescott's favorite hamburger and noodles
directions: Brown ground beef, add onion and cook until translucent; drain.
Add mushrooms, soup and sour cream. Place over cooked noodles.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: date oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend sugars, butter, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and salt; beat well.
Combine flour, oats and baking soda; add to butter mixture. Mix well.
Add dates and nuts, if desired.
Drop by spoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.
Combine rest of ingredients and beat 10 to 15 minutes until light and fluffy.
Spread on cooled cake.
Microwave 1 can prepared chocolate frosting (opened) for approximately 1 minute on High.
Pour over filling and spread with knife.
Serves 12 at 586 calories per 1/12th piece.

title: meemee's maple peanut butter yummies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Cream the shortening and peanut butter together.
Add brown sugar; cream well.
Add maple syrup and egg yolk; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into balls.
Place on ungreased pan and flatten with fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: all saints' day bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add margarine, sugar, salt and beaten eggs.
Cool to lukewarm.
Crumble or sprinkle yeast in milk mixture.
Leave set until bubbly (a few minutes).
Add the liquid mixture to flour in a large bowl.
Add more flour as needed (should hardly be sticky). Add a few raisins.
Let raise until double in bulk.
Then knead bread and divide into sections.
Hand roll sections.
Cut into small pieces.
Roll out and braid.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cheese and onions
directions: Slice onions into shallow pan.
Add a knob of butter and enough water to keep them from burning.
Cook until transparent, over a low fire.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan; press out 1 package crescent rolls.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla together and spread over pressed crescent rolls.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine.
Bake for 2 hours at 250°, or cook slowly on cooktop, until thick.

title: mardi gras king cake
directions: Will need a 1-inch China baby doll.

title: basque potatoes
directions: Cover potato cubes with water.
Let stand while preparing sauce.
Melt butter or margarine in large pan.
Add onion, garlic, celery and carrots; saute until vegetables are limp.
Drain potatoes and add to vegetables.
Mix thoroughly.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in the boiling water.
Add to potatoes along with salt.
Cover, lower heat and simmer slowly until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Pour into tureen and sprinkle with parsley.
Very low in calories.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Cook at 425° for 10 minutes, then cook at 350° until done.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Put in oiled baking dish.

title: fluffy duffy
directions: First Layer:
Melt margarine in pan.
Add flour and nuts. Press out to fit pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and let cool.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, beans, salt, onion, cheese, soup and sour cream. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix crackers, almonds and melted margarine.
Spread over vegetable mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/4 cups of boiling water.
Add partially frozen strawberries and sugar. Cool until mixture starts to thicken.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of 9-inch pan with torn pieces of cake.
Pour half of strawberry mixture over the cake. Continue with second layer of cake pieces and remainder of strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: pot roast
directions: Mix catsup, water and soup mix together. Pour over roast and bake until done. May use cooking bag. Bake at 350°F, 20 minutes per pound.

title: rainbow finger jello
directions: For each jello layer:
Mix one box jello with 1 envelope Knox. Add 1 cup very hot water; stir until dissolved.
Pour into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry-pineapple dessert salad
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.
May be served as a sweet salad or put in a graham cracker crust for a dessert.

title: upside-down apple pie
directions: Arrange nuts, flat sides up, in butter in deep 9-inch pie pan.
Pat brown sugar over nuts and cover with a thick circle or pastry, 1/8 inch thick.
Trim edges.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon into pastry.
Cover with top crust.
Bake in pre-heated moderate over (350°) for about 40 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes. Serve warm, plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: italian seasoned potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Melt oleo and mix together with Good Seasons Italian seasoning.
Add to potatoes in a long cake pan.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: edee's vegetable soup
directions: Place all in a large pan.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add 1 small head of cabbage and simmer another hour.
The more you reheat, the better it is.

title: cottage cheese salad or dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatine in hot water.
Add cold water.
Add sugar, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix in nuts, pineapple and vanilla. Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir until melted.
Drain pineapple well.
Add to Jell-O and cranberry sauce.
Add celery and nuts.
Stir well.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: barbecued round steak
directions: Wash and tenderize meat.
Cut into small pieces and place in ovenproof dish.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
Use lid or foil to cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
You can have it more tender by baking it at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cher's pumpkin pancakes
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Beat together the egg whites and low-fat buttermilk.
Stir in the pumpkin.
Add to dry ingredients and blend well.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, mashed bananas, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Blend well and add nuts.
Pour batter in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tortellini and artichokes in garlic and cream sauce
directions: In large saucepan over high heat, bring water and salt to a boil.
Drop tortellini into boiling water.
Return to boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook 20 to 25 minutes until tortellini are tender.
Drain.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add syrup, sugar and butter.
Mix well. Add pecans and mix.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Pie is done when a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: easy casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Layer potatoes, carrots, raw onion and hamburger meat.
Top with the soups.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: tuna salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Makes about one cup (enough for three sandwiches).
Spread on bread and garnish with lettuce and tomato.
Contains 247 calories and 5 fat grams per sandwich.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Empty both cans of pie filling into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle lemon juice over cherries.
Place cake mix in mixing bowl; gradually add melted butter to cake mix; stir and mix well until cake and butter are mixed.
Cake mix will become crumbly. Sprinkle/spread cake mixture over top of cherries.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: onion-dill dip
directions: In food processor, whip cottage cheese to the consistency of sour cream.
Add all remaining ingredients except chopped onion and blend well.
Remove from processor and add onion.
Flavor is better if allowed to chill before serving.
Entire recipe makes 2 servings.

title: chicken salad filling
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Ready to spread on sandwiches.

title: apple relish
directions: Mix and bake in moderate oven for one hour.

title: western kentucky's cheese grits
directions: Bring water to boil, add grits slowly and cook 3 to 5 minutes. Remove from stove; add salt, garlic to taste (sparingly), cheese and butter.
Beat eggs in a one-cup measure and fill cup to top with milk.
Add to grits.
Place in casserole; sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: dear abby's pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over filling.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Toast walnuts in 350° oven until golden (8 to 10 minutes). Blend cheeses.
Stir in garlic salt, pimiento and green pepper. Chill until firm.
Shape into ball and roll in toasted walnuts. Chill until serving time.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Blend in next 3 ingredients, then flour and soda.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Allow to melt and spread as frosting.
