Cut into 1 x 3-inch fingers.

title: riverboat chicken and shrimp
directions: Heat fat; add onion and cook until soft. Blend in flour; add broth and chicken, shrimp, mushrooms, almonds and parsley. Stir until slightly thickened. Season with celery salt and sherry, if desired. Serve in patty shell.

title: sauteed crab cakes
directions: Combine crab meat, salt and pepper.
In a small saucepan, cook the bell pepper in 3 tablespoons butter over medium-low heat, stirring until softened.
Remove pan from heat.
Stir in lemon juice, beaten egg and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir the mixture into the crab meat.
Add chopped egg and bread crumbs.
Combine gently, but thoroughly.
Form into 4 patties.
Heat oil and remaining butter.
Saute crab cakes, turning them after 4 to 5 minutes until golden brown and crisp.
Add more oil and butter to pan if necessary to prevent sticking.
Serve with tartar sauce.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended; refrigerate.
Serve with chips, crackers or vegetable dippers.

title: grilled carrots
directions: Heat coals in outdoor grill until hot.
Lightly oil or coat grill rack with nonstick vegetable cooking spray and set aside.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Butter the sides of a 2-quart saucepan.
Mix and bring to a boil the sugar, butter, milk and cocoa.
Boil hard 1 minute.
Add to oatmeal.
Mix; let cool for a couple of minutes.
Spoon onto foil in cookie-size mounds.

title: strawberry cherub cake(cake in a bowl)
directions: Mix gelatin and berries, thicken until thick as pudding. Place first layer of cake in a very large bowl (punch).
Spoon in gelatin, then pudding and top with Cool Whip.
Continue until all layers are completed.
Chill until set.
Serves 20+.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Spoon into greased, deep baking dish.
Bake at 325 degrees for one hour.

title: brunch:  angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar together; cut in shortening and add buttermilk and yeast.
Knead lightly, cut in desired size and turn in greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Do not let rise.
If not baked immediately, store in refrigerator.
Makes 50 servings.

title: very cherry sundaes
directions: In 1-quart casserole, cook cherries or canned cherries plus 2 tablespoons sugar, covered, on high heat for 4 to 5 minutes, until hot.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Stir in 1 tablespoon brandy (optional).

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in greased square pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix milk, oleo, sugar,
coconut
and pecans; shape into small balls.
Arrange on wax paper
and
chill 20 minutes.
In double boiler, cook chocolate chips, Hershey bars and paraffin until all is melted.
Take
first
mixture out of refrigerator and
dip into melted
chocolate
mixture.
Use
toothpicks
in balls and dip in chocolate or use
candy
spoon and set out on wax paper.

title: strawberries chantilly
directions: Hull berries and arrange in bowl.
Whip cream until foamy and barely thickened.
Fold in chocolate, confectioners sugar and rum. Chill.
Serve as sauce for strawberries.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sugarless dried apple cake
directions: Cook
apples
until
tender
and
drain
off water. Add raisins and
walnuts.
Combine dry ingredients and then cut in diet margarine. Add dry ingredients to apple mixture, then add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour batter into tube pan or coffee cake pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: good and easy icing
directions: Combine pudding, sugar and milk in a small bowl.
Beat on lowest speed about 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread on cooled cake.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Using a 9-inch pie pan, bake crust for 5 to 7 minutes, or until very light golden brown.
Remove from oven, and let cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Meanwhile, cut candy bars in half lengthwise, then cut into 1/4-inch pieces. Place candy bar pieces over bottom of partially baked crust.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Substitute:
Can add 1 (12 ounce) package peanut butter chips.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt all ingredients in saucepan or microwave, stirring frequently.
Serve warm with plain tortilla chips.
Keep covered in refrigerator.
Will keep 1 to 2 months.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine ingredients in dish and serve.

title: carrot rice
directions: Bring water to boil, Add chicken bouillon cube. Let dissolve. Stir in carrot and rice. Bring back to boil, reduce heat to med low. Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.

title: mexican dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend all other ingredients in.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Serve with Favorite chips.

title: party apple dip
directions: Mix together with electric beater.
Top with chopped nuts. Dip with sliced apples.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil whole chicken in water with small amount of salt.
Cool. Save broth.
When cool, skim off fat.
Remove chicken from bones and cut meat into smaller pieces.

title: cola cake
directions: Mix margarine, cocoa and cola, then bring to a boil.
Mix with flour, sugar, sour milk and baking soda.
Mix in marshmallows. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: savory crescent chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend the cheese and 2 tablespoons of margarine (reserve 1 tablespoon).
Add the next 6 ingredients. Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup into the center.
Twist the dough firmly together.
Brush the tops with margarine and dip into crouton crumbs.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lazy woman chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased baking pan.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
Put oil in one, vanilla in one and vinegar in one, then pour water over it all. Stir with fork until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: low-fat thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in advance.
Store in refrigerator; use as needed over all sorts of salads.

title: cheese and pastry appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Muenster, egg, pepper, garlic salt, salt and butter/margarine.
Set aside.
Roll out 1/4 package of the crescent rolls into a rectangle.
Be sure to seal pieces together.
Place half the cheese mixture in the center of the pastry and spread evenly, leaving about a 1/2 inch border all the way around the rectangle.
Roll out another 1/4 of the package into a rectangle; again being sure to seam pieces together and place on top of cheese mixture.
Pinch the pastry layers together, fluting decoratively as for pie crust if you wish.
Cut a few slits in the top for steam to escape and bake for about 20 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.
This is good warm or at room temperature. Repeat process with remaining crescent rolls and filling to make an additional borka.

title: garlic oregano chicken
directions: Place chicken in oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix remaining ingredients, except lemon slices; pour over chicken.
Cook, uncovered, in a 375° oven, spooning oil mixture over chicken occasionally, for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; cook until thickest pieces are done, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Heat jelly and preserves until thin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve by pouring over a softened 8 ounce package of cream cheese with your favorite crackers or cocktail bread on the side.
May also be served as a condiment with pork or lamb.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of an 11 x 17-inch baking pan (jelly roll pan) with the sheets of crescent rolls, patting and stretching to fit pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or lightly browned.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Sift and measure flour, then sift again with baking powder and salt.
Add alternately to creamed mixture, the dry ingredients and evaporated milk.
Add maple flavoring and vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 300° in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours or until straw inserted comes out clean.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream first four ingredients well; add eggs one at a time and beat well with mixer after each egg is added.
Stir together flour and baking powder; add to cream mixture, alternating with milk. Add flavoring and beat well.
Bake in a large tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: oven smothered steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces; coat with flour, seasoned with seasoning salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides.
Place in baking dish and pour mushroom soup over meat.
Place sliced onions and bell peppers on top.
Drain excess oil from pan where steak was browned.
Make roux with flour and seasoning salt; brown.
Add water.
Pour over steak.
Cover with foil and cook in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: best peach pie
directions: Put peaches, sugar, 1 heaping tablespoonful flour, water and butter in boiler.
Cook until peaches are done and juice is thick. Set aside.
Combine 1 cup flour, Crisco and buttermilk and mix together for your crust.
Halve the dough mixture.
On a floured surface, roll out thin.
Put peach mixture in Pyrex dish.
Put crust on top.
Put in oven and brown crust.
Add remainder of peach mixture to dish.
Roll out remaining dough.
Cover pie with top crust, either lattice type or solid crust.
You may sprinkle lightly with sugar if preferred.
Bake at 425° until crust is brown.

title: joy's berry easy jello salad
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan or any size of your choice.

title: cherry pink sponge salad
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Whip the cream; add all ingredients together and put in fancy bowl to serve.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Brown sausage through.
Drain grease.
In casserole, layer:
spaghetti, sausage, Parmesan and Ragu sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Heat until all ingredients are heated thoroughly and cheese melted.

title: skillet hamburgers
directions: Cook mushrooms in saucepan.
Fry hamburgers; drain off excess grease.
Cover hamburgers with mushrooms and steam in a covered skillet for 20 minutes and serve.

title: fruit dip 1
directions: Mix marshmallow cream and cream cheese together well.
I add the jello for more flavor.
Use as a dip for fresh fruit.

title: hamburger french onion soup
directions: Brown butter in the bottom of your soup kettle.
Add the hamburger and fry until very brown and well separated.
Add slices of onions, consomme, water and bouillon cubes; simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with squares of buttered toast topped with Parmesan cheese.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla; stir until well blended.
Stir in pecans. Pour into frozen pie crust.
Bake on a preheated baking sheet 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.
tags: Pet-Ritz deep dish frozen pie crust

title: haystack salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato sticks.
Chill several hours before serving.
Add potato sticks just before serving.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place meat
in	large
glass dish.
Mix all ingredients except fat, in
a saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over meat. Cover and refrigerate for 48 to 72 hours, turning meat several times to season evenly.
Remove meat, reserving marinade.
Dry meat well with paper towels.

title: rhubarb pie(not the reunion kind)
directions: Stir together flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until flour forms small pea shapes.
Add 1 Tbsp. of water at a time gently tossing with a fork.
Repeat until all dough is moistened.
Form into a ball,
Flatten with floured hands on floured surface, then use rolling pin to flatten the rest of the way.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine vegetables, salt and ice and put in stone crock; cover with weighted lid and let stand 3 hours, then drain.
Combine sugar, spices and vinegar.
Pour over pickles in large enamel kettle (aluminum or stainless).
Bring to boiling point over low heat.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar, milk and butter.
Boil for 15 minutes over medium heat; stir frequently.
Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallow cream.
Stir in butterscotch and chocolate chips; stir until melted.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) buttered dishes.

title: vegetarian biscuitsdallas, texas
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together. Cut in shortening and then add the milk.
Blend together just till mixed.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1/2-inch pieces.
Beat eggs; pour over rhubarb.
Mix sugar and flour; mix with rhubarb.
Stir until rhubarb is well coated.
Place in 2 pie shells.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then turn temperature to 350° and continue to bake for 30 minutes more.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower, broccoli and celery until tender; drain. Saute onion in oleo until tender.
Mix all ingredients together in large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Add flour.
Cook and stir on low heat until dark red-brown.
Add remaining ingredients (except rice).
Cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Combine with rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, reserving 3/4 c. of noodles.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 325 degrees for 40 min.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix and spread over greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth.
Pour in a graham cracker crust and chill.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix.
Drop from a funnel into hot oil, making a circular shape.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and any other fruit topping.

title: green beans and almonds
directions: Pat beans and chopped onions in baking dish.
Put sugar, vinegar and almonds in bacon drippings.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over beans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: millionaire pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease and flour a large Bundt pan.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add extract, milk, flour and salt. Blend well.
Pour into pan and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out and pour glaze over hot cake.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Beat egg whites.
Slowly add sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order given.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except whipping cream, and cook until thick. Cool overnight. Whip the cream and fold into the above. Serve with fruit of your choice. Makes 2 cups.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Add next 2 ingredients. Bring to 260°.
Remove from heat and add last 2 ingredients.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour in a shallow buttered pan.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, salt, 1/4 cup margarine, milk and vanilla.
Spoon into ungreased 1 to 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine brown sugar, flour, nuts and 3 tablespoons margarine; spread over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar, oil, water, salt and pepper.
Cool. Combine vegetables and pour liquid over them.
Mix and refrigerate. Keeps well.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Mix first three ingredients and let stand overnight.
The next morning, cook until tender (about 20 minutes).
Add strawberry gelatin and mix.

title: diabetic sugarless cookies
directions: Boil raisins, dates and apples in 1/3 cup water for 3 minutes. Add shortening, then cool.
Add beaten eggs, liquid sweetener and vanilla.
Sift flour and soda together; mix into the mixture.
Add nuts and chill.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry with paper towels.
In a large pot, brown chicken in oleo on both sides.
Remove from heat.
Add onion, celery, carrot, lemon, black pepper and bay leaf.
Cover with boiling water.
Bring to a boil; then reduce heat and cover. Let simmer 45 minutes.
Add salt; cook, covered, one hour until chicken is tender.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and set overnight.
Pour salt over cukes and let stand 1/2 hour.
Wash with cold water and drain.
Add to the mixture.
Keep in glass container such as large canning jars or large glass jars.
Let stand 24 hours before using.
Great served with any type meats roasted, broiled or grilled.
Can be used for 6 months.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool and add ginger ale. When nearly set, add fruit.

title: pasta pizza
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Mix eggs, milk and Parmesan.
Stir into macaroni.
Spray a 12-inch pizza pan with nonstick spray coating.
Spread macaroni mixture evenly in pan. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cream-cheese pumpkin cake
directions: In large bowl, let eggs warm to room temperature (about 30 minutes).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with baking soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
At high speed, beat eggs with sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in oil and pumpkin to blend well.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture just until combined.
Pour
into ungreased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake about 1 hour or until surface springs back when gently pressed with fingertip.
Cool cake completely in pan.
With spatula, carefully loosen cake from pan; remove.
Place cake on plate.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Decorate with nuts.
Makes 12 servings.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add flour, eggs and milk; beat well.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before slicing.

title: heavenly pears
directions: Toast almonds and butter in microwave until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Drain the pear halves and arrange in a circular dish with the large ends of the pears at the outer edge of the container.
Mix almonds, sugar, almond extract and maraschino cherries.
Spoon into the pear cavities.
Put 1 teaspoon wine in each pear cavity and pour the rest into the baking dish.
Microwave covered on High 4 minutes.
Pears can be served hot or chilled. Serve 5 to 6.

title: marinated ham biscuits
directions: Melt butter; add mustard, poppy seed and onion, mix well. Split rolls; spread both sides.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Spread thinly sliced ham on rolls and cheese (Cheddar), about 15 slices.
Place in oven.
Heat at 350° for about 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Can be made and frozen.
Makes 40 rolls.

title: pork chops with grapes
directions: Season pork chops and spread one side with mustard.
Heat butter in a skillet and brown the chops mustard side up.
Turn and brown the mustard side and spread browned side with mustard.
Add grapes to the pan and shake it.
Cover and simmer over low heat until chops are tender and cooked through.
Remove the chops to a warm platter.
Skim most of the fat from the dripping.
Add sour cream to pan and heat but do not boil.
Pour sauce over meat. Serves 4.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and
cornstarch
together.
Add
the milk. Cook until thickened.
Add gelatine that
has been softened in a little cold water.
When partly set, add
coconut, flavoring and beaten egg whites. Pour into baked pie shells.
Sprinkle top with coconut.

title: ginger asparagus with cashews
directions: Trim off the tough, lower stems of the asparagus and discard. Cut each stalk into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Heat the oils in a preheated wok or large frying pan over a high heat.
Add the asparagus and ginger and stir fry until tender crisp, about 4-5 minutes.
Stir in the orange peel, soy sauce and cashews.
Serve immediately.

title: mom's tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain well.
Add all the other ingredients together, except half of the grated cheese. Stir macaroni and remaining ingredients well; put in a 9 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until cheese on top is well melted.

title: sausage-sauerkraut rolls
directions: Thaw frozen rolls on wax paper.
Cook sausage.
Drain.
Add sauerkraut (drained).
Cool.
Grease hands.
Make circles 2 to 3 inches from thawed rolls.
Fill with sausage and sauerkraut mixture.
Fold over and lay bottom side down on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: school sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple syrup.
Add sugar to cranberries; let stand.
Add all ingredients to jello when it becomes syrupy thick.
Chill in mold.

title: baked chili rellenos
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain well.
Add salt and pepper.
Put half chilies in a 6x10 baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, add meat mixture.
Add remainder of chilies and cheese.
Combine milk, flour, salt and eggs.
Pour batter on chili meat mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cut into squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain.
Add salt, pepper and sugar. Add 1/2 package of stuffing mix, sour cream, soup, grated carrot and pimento.
Mix well.
In 9 x 13-inch Pyrex casserole dish, melt stick of margarine.
Remove from oven and pour in remaining bag of stuffing mix and mix with margarine until damp.
Reserve half of stuffing.
Pour first mixture (squash) over crumb mixture, spread until smooth and top with remaining crumbs. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sticky rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough 3 minutes in microwave until it can be cut, but not soft.
Slice 1/2-inch thick quarter slices.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan, layer 1 loaf bread dough pieces.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix and melt other 4 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 over dough and cinnamon.
Repeat with rest of dough, cinnamon and mixture.
Cover with dish towel and stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and flip over onto wax paper.
Serve.

title: aunt dot's sour cream corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients. Bake in a 9-inch cast iron skillet for 35 minutes or more.
Green peppers, onions, cheese or any other ingredients can be added if you prefer.

title: quick french pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over vegetables; cover and let stand for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Drain off liquid.
Mix vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Do not heat.
Pour over cucumber mixture after sugar is dissolved.
Cover in airtight container and store in refrigerator. Keeps for several weeks.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes in greased pan.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Chop all vegetables; set aside.
Cook vermicelli according to package directions (break into 1 to 2-inch pieces before cooking). Drain and rinse in cool water.
Toss vermicelli with Italian dressing.
Mix in all vegetables.
Sprinkle and stir in salad seasoning.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Toss and serve.
(Also good while warm.)

title: pot roast
directions: Rub meat with flour, salt and pepper.
Melt suet in a heavy kettle or Dutch oven.
Add meat; sear.
Add water, cover tightly and cook slowly about 4 hours or until tender.
More water may be used, if necessary.
Makes 8 servings.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cut pineapple and cherries into small pieces.
Cream Crisco and brown sugar lightly.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° until light brown, about 15 minutes.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil; simmer.
Remove spices.
Good on a cold winter day.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Stir 5 minutes over medium heat to soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all together well.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons to each cup hot water.

title: punch
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and freeze.
Add ginger ale.

title: old time yankee apple cake
directions: Use tart apples with lots of flavor.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter into mixture, add egg and milk; mix well.
Pour dough into 8-inch pan and cover top with rows of apple slices.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with Lemon Sauce.

title: angel cream cake
directions: Combine dessert topping and milk; beat well.
Add powdered sugar and cream cheese; beat.
Cut cake into 3 layers.
Place 1 layer on cake plate; spread with layer of topping mixture.
Repeat layers.
Frost top and sides; sprinkle with almonds and cherries. Refrigerate.
Garnish with stemmed cherries.

title: almond cookies
directions: Mix together.
Cook in slow oven at 325° until done, 15 minutes.

title: social baked beans
directions: Mix together gently.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; add to the sugar mixture, stirring well.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Spoon batter into a 9-inch square pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool on a wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
16 brownies; per brownie 177 calories and fat 5.8 g.

title: one layer chocolate cake
directions: In
a large mixer bowl, combine the flour, sugar, cocoa powder,
baking
powder,
baking soda and salt.
Add the milk, shortening
and
vanilla.
Beat
the
mixture with an electric mixer on low speed until combined.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add
the egg and beat for 2 minutes more.
Pour into a greased
and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool
on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan.
Cool
thoroughly.
Frost with No Cook Fudge Frosting.

title: frozen fruit pie
directions: Stir flour and sugar in large saucepan. Add cherries and pineapple. Bring to a boil; cool 5 minutes. Add jello, bananas and pecans. Pour into 3 cooked pie crusts. Freeze. Thaw during meal; top with whipped topping and eat while frosty.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Put sugar, flour and juice on stove.
When starting to melt, add pineapple and 1 cup shredded cheese.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Add 1/2 cup melted oleo. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: honey-glazed new potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, cover potatoes with salted water.
Bring water to a boil and cook until potatoes are tender; drain.
In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in water, honey, salt and pepper.
Stirring occasionally, cook 1 layer of potatoes 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Transfer to serving dish and cover with aluminum foil to keep warm.
Repeat for remaining potatoes.
Serve warm.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Mix soda and spices with sifted flour.
Combine with sugar mixture.
Roll in balls.
Not necessary to grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberries with raspberry sauce
directions: Combine the cornstarch and liqueur in a small saucepan.
Stir over low heat until the mixture simmers and thickens.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in long baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk together.
Pour over melted butter.
Put peaches on top.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease bottom of 12 muffin pan cups.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan. Mix other ingredients except cheese together. Add cheese to top. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of pan. Mix together all remaining ingredients.
Bake on middle rack at 325° for 1 hour.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon (reserving liquid) and flake in medium bowl. Add onion, butter, cracker crumbs, eggs (reserving 1 egg white) and Tabasco sauce. Mix, adding more crumbs or liquid to make a firm patty. Whip egg white a few strokes with a few drops of water in a sauce dish large enough to roll the patties. In another sauce dish, have cracker crumbs. Form patties (burger size), dipping in egg white, then rolling in the crumbs to coat. Put pan on medium-low heat, adding butter. Add the patties and brown on both sides. Takes only a few minutes. Serve with lemon.

title: seafood delight
directions: Mix all together and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grape-raisin blush
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth. Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: old-fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix very slow by hand.
Brown sugar, flour, milk and egg until blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until middle is set.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Add confectioners sugar to water and bring to a boil.
Boil until clarifies (approximately 2 minutes) and remove from heat. Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla extract.
Stir rapidly until uniform in color.
Before mixing sets, pour into a 9-inch baking pan (greased) and agitate to distribute evenly.
Add chocolate chips on top.
Place in refrigerator until firm, approximately 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: coconut drop cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and lard together.
Add milk and vanilla. Sift all dry ingredients together and add.
Put icing on top and flaked coconut (m-m-m-m).
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: ginger tea
directions: Mix and serve over ice.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Line large baking pan (9 x 13-inch or larger) with aluminum foil.
Dot with butter.
Place steak pieces in pan, then sprinkle with onion soup mix, fresh mushrooms, green peppers and tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper.
Mix together tomato juice, A1. steak sauce and cornstarch; pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover pan tightly with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut up beef in bite size pieces.
Put all ingredients in a large, covered casserole or Dutch oven.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours; stir occasionally.
May add more wine or water if mixture seems dry.
Serve over boiled noodles.

title: sugar snap peas with baby onions
directions: Thaw onions and peas.
Ten minutes before ready to serve, cook them together in a small amount of water until onions are crisp and tender.
Drain; add butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with pimento.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown beef with onion and green chilies in the microwave, approximately 5 to 8 minutes, or until not pink.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer corn tortillas, meat, cheese, soup mixture and enchilada sauce.
Repeat, with cheese last.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coffee bread
directions: Thaw loaf of bread dough until frost free.
Cut into 1 inch cubes or smaller.
Mix package of pudding, brown sugar, butter, nuts, cinnamon and vanilla until crumbly.
Layer with bread dough cubes in Bundt pan.
Let rise until almost double.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Remove from pan by turning upside down on plate.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 9-inch deep dish pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Put top crust on and use fork to make air vents
in
top	crust.	Bake at 350° about an hour or until golden brown.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Pour eggs, milk, baking powder and vanilla over bread.	Cover and refrigerate overnight. In the morning, combine the strawberries, bananas, sugar and apple pie spice. Put in greased baking dish and top with prepared bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Bake in 450° oven 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese apple salad(waldorf salad with cheese)
directions: Blend lemon juice and salt into sour cream.
Chill.
Cut unpared apples into thin slices; sprinkle with additional lemon juice.
(For a more colorful salad, use a combination of red and green apples.)
Add Swiss and Cheddar cheese, celery, grapes and walnuts; toss together.
Just before serving, fold in the sour cream to blend.
Serve on salad greens, garnished with apple slices and grapes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: layered fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: tomato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring tomatoes to a boil.
Add baking soda, garlic salt, pepper and salt, if desired.
Reduce heat; add the milk and butter.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Makes 6 servings.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix together; chill overnight.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix everything together and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in a 10-inch greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes. Check before time is up.
Cool for 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool on rack.
Split into 3 layers and slice.
Spread 1 cup frosting between layers (1/2 cup each layer).
Spoon rest of frosting into center.
Sprinkle nuts over cake.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook ground beef.
Drain off excess fat.
Add Prego sauce to beef.
Place biscuits in an 8 x 10-inch dish.
Pour beef and Prego sauce over uncooked biscuits.
Add cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes until brown.
"Delicious."
May add onions and peppers if you like.

title: buttermilk buns
directions: Heat buttermilk until it separates and is warm.
Combine sugar and salt with buttermilk in large mixing bowl.
Dissolve yeast in mixture; stir in egg.
Add shortening; add half the flour, stirring well.
Add remaining flour gradually, stirring until dough leaves side of bowl.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth and place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Punch dough down; shape into rolls.
Place on sheet.
Let rise in warm place.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry almond sauce(for pork roast or pork chops)
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Heat to boiling; stir frequently.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes.
Add almonds. Spoon over meat as meat is cooking.
Return roast to oven for 30 minutes.
Baste several times.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, add vegetables if desired.
Combine soup, milk and parsley; set aside.
In 2 or 3-quart baking dish, arrange stuffing across center of dish.
Spoon thin layer of soup mixture in casserole on each side of stuffing.
Arrange chicken over soup mixture.
Pour remaining mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes.
Uncover, bake 10 minutes more or until chicken is fork-tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: gladys starr's spoon bread
directions: Stir corn meal into 2 cups of milk and let mixture come to a boil, making a mush.
Add balance of milk and add well-beaten eggs.
Stir in salt, baking powder and melted butter.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bake and cool pie shells.
Put a thin layer of peanut butter in the bottom of the pie shells.
Blend the rest of the peanut butter, whipping cream and vanilla pudding in a bowl with mixer until fluffy.
Spoon into pie shells.
Refrigerate about an hour.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Beat egg and milk, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Put cracker crumbs and cheese in paper sack.
Dip eggplant into egg mixture and then into cracker crumbs.
Coat well.
Fry in deep hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel and serve hot. Squash, cauliflower, broccoli or any vegetable may be done the same way.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook frozen chopped broccoli according to directions on package.
Then mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, then add vinegar, beet juice and margarine. Cook until clear red. Pour beets into mixture and simmer 5 minutes or until beets are heated through.

title: party pink salad
directions: Mix oranges and pineapple with jello until dissolved.
Add cream cheese, Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: devilish ham spread
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together mayonnaise, relish and onion. Add ham, cheese and celery.
Stir until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Serve on crackers.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Put rice in casserole dish which has a lid.
Mix soup and milk together in a bowl.
Mix 2/3 of this mixture with rice in casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice.
Pour rest of soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, then 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour alternately with sour cream and lemon juice.
Add vanilla and lemon rind.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.

title: mississippi slide
directions: Mix oleo, chopped pecans and flour.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Then take cream cheese (softened), powdered sugar and Cool Whip and mix these together.
Spread over baked crust.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs slightly in a large bowl and then add all other ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, covered, at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add partially thawed strawberries, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Fill dish/mold half full.
Let congeal.
Spread sour cream over jello mixture and spoon remaining mixture over sour cream.
Return to refrigerator.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift together flour and red pepper.
Put cheese and margarine through food chopper.
Gradually work flour into cheese and shortening until smooth, if possible.
Pinch off pieces and roll into marble size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Center each one with a small piece of pecan.
Press down to anchor the nut.
Bake in 400° oven for about 9 minutes.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: baked beets
directions: Dice beets in casserole. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over beets. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy cherry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pour pie filling into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a small bowl, combine flour and butter.
Blend with pastry blender or fork.
Add sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon. Mix well and sprinkle over cherries. Bake for 30 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Butter baking pan.
In medium bowl mix fruit and 1/2 cup sugar until sugar dissolves.
Pour in pan.
In large bowl, mix 1 cup sugar, butter, egg and vanilla.
Spread over fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serve with topping or ice cream.
Serves 4.

title: turkey rice casserole
directions: One hour and 45 minutes ahead, preheat oven to 350°.
In 2 1/2-quart casserole, stir turkey, undiluted soup, milk, celery, rice, vermouth and parsley.
Cover casserole and bake 1 1/2 hours, stirring once or twice, until rice is cooked and mixture is hot and bubbly.

title: donna's killer barbecue sauce
directions: Chop onion and pepper; saute in a little butter.
Add other ingredients and let simmer.
Brown your meat and put your meat in sauce and cook slowly.

title: stuff and such chicken casserole
directions: Combine Stuff and Such according to directions on package. Make crust in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put chicken on top.
Mix cream of chicken and milk and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with parsley. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream.
Heat. Serve as sauce for casserole.

title: cucumbers with onions
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Add cucumber and onion. Chill 30 to 60 minutes.

title: quick chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets heavy-duty plastic wrap; flatten to 1/4-inch thick with a rolling pin. Dip chicken in egg and then bread crumbs. Melt butter in a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray over medium heat. Add chicken and cook 4 minutes on each side or until browned. Spoon pasta sauce over chicken; cover, decrease heat and simmer, covered, 10 minutes. Sprinkle with cheeses and parsley; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Spoon 3/4 cup pasta on 4 plates; top each with a chicken breast and divide sauce evenly. Makes 4 servings.

title: easy onion popovers
directions: Blend eggs, milk, onion, salt and oil. Add flour, beat until smooth. Beat one minute in electric mixer, or 3 minutes with rotary mixer. Fill well greased custard cups 1/2 full. Bake 400° for 40-45 minutes till golden, firm.

title: cream of wheat cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased large skillet and bake 30 minutes at 400° or until done.

title: chex party mix
directions: In a small bowl, mix seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce with melted butter and mix well.
Pour cereals, nuts and pretzels into a Ziploc bag.
Pour sauce mixture over cereal mixture in bag.
Seal bag securely.
Shake well, until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour contents of bag into large microwave safe bowl. Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes.
Spread out on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Pour into prepared pie crust and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes.
You may add more spice.

title: diabetic strawberry shake
directions: Add ingredients in order listed in blender. Puree at medium speed until thick and smooth.
Makes 2 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: dump cake
directions: After greasing a 9 x 12-inch pan, place ingredients in pan as listed.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until top is brown.
Serve from pan.

title: brandy cake
directions: Combine and mix for 3 minutes.
Pour into well-greased pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, depending on size of pan.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Cut bread crisscross (not all the way through).
Mix shredded cheese with sliced mushrooms.
Stuff bread with mixture.
Melt butter, mix in onions, lemon juice and spices.
Spoon on top of cheese and mushroom stuffing.
Wrap loaf in foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: 3 cheese chicken
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add mushrooms, pimentos, milk and mushroom soup to onion mixture.
In large casserole, layer noodles, chicken and onion and pepper sauce. Layer cottage cheese, then Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Shred carrots.
Soak raisins in lemon juice.
Combine ingredients; mix with dressing.
Serve in lettuce cups.

title: white beans
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Keep 3 cups liquid.
Add bouillon cubes.
Rinse pork, dry and cut into 1-inch strips. Brown in oil until crispy.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours, or until beans are tender.
Good in crock-pot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add sugar and oil.
Mix; stir in zucchini.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in until moistened.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir gently.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle cinnamon.
Pat with margarine.
Bake at 325° until pie is firm. Makes 1 pie.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Put poppy seed and milk in bowl and let soak for 1 hour.
Mix oleo and sugar until blended.
Add milk and poppy seed.
Then add baking powder in flour.
Add to sugar mixture and vanilla.
Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Fold in with the other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with Custard Frosting.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes until firm.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Put chicken in
greased
x 9-inch pan.
Combine soup and wine, stir.
Spoon over chicken, then sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Next
top
with
a layer of cheese.
Drizzle margarine over top and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: mel and lil's dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Put dill weed in bottom of quart jars.
Put grape leaf in bottom of each jar.
Next, put 2 pieces of raw garlic in each.
Pinch of pickling spice next. Fill jars with cucumbers.
Leave about 1 1/2-inches in top.
Mix water, vinegar and salt together.
Pour on top of cucumbers.
Leave 1/2-inch. Seal with new jar lids.
Cold pack 5 minutes.
Let set 2 weeks.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Good with pumpernickel bread.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together.
Use approximately 2 to 3 tablespoons mixture to 1 cup hot water.

title: german coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and
add	sugar.	In
saucepan
add
oil, vinegar, honey, salt, prepared mustard and celery seed.
Bring all to boil.
Pour over cabbage.
Let refrigerate overnight.

title: stir and fry vegetables
directions: Toss vegetables lightly.
Add oil to skillet.
Add vegetables and cook in covered skillet for 10 minutes, stirring twice.

title: shrimp peioleau
directions: Cut okra, bell pepper and onion in small pieces.
Saute with shrimp in saucepan after frying 4 strips of bacon (drain oil from pan, leaving bacon strips in, cut in small pieces).
Wash rice, leaving small amount of water after washing.
Put all ingredients in baking pan or dish.
Add tomato sauce.
Season to taste.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
After one hour, stir.
Turn oven off, leaving pan in oven until oven cools.

title: broiled onion-tomatoes
directions: Place tomato halves in broiler pan or on aluminum foil. Spread each with mustard and top with onion rings.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Broil 3 minutes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix together green beans, soup, salt and pepper.
Place in rectangular glass casserole.
Add pats of butter over top and sprinkle with onions.
Bake at 400° until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan except for the sprinkles; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
After mixture comes to a boil, cook for 5 minutes until thickened.
Pour into glass dish and refrigerate overnight.
Butter hands and roll into balls.
Roll in chocolate sprinkles.
Yields approximately 24 balls.

title: lois webster's sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream oil and butter with sugar, add vanilla and eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients and stir in.
Roll dough by teaspoonful making a ball.
Press down on cookie sheet with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake about 12 minutes at 325°.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoon in hot oil.
Cook until brown.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Place on top of cooled first layer.
Pour pie filling on top of both layers.
Serve.

title: jule kag(norwegian)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour scalded milk over butter. Add yeast and sugar; add 1/2 flour and salt.
Beat well for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add fruit and remaining flour.
Knead and place in greased bowl to rise.
Cover and place in warm place.
Dough should be cool to touch.
When doubled, knead again and rise again.
Shape into loaves and place into greased pans.
Brush tops with egg whites. When doubled bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Brush crust with melted butter, sugar and cinnamon.

title: marvelous nutty marbled cheese delight
directions: To make crust, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Press 3/4 of this into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Bake the remaining 1/4 of the mixture separately and crumble to save for a top garnish.

title: bread sticks
directions: Spread on all sides of bread, except the brown side.
Place in preheated oven at 200° and bake for 2 hours.

title: salmon supreme
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove dark skin from the salmon.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve with crackers and any vegetables.

title: breakfast before
directions: Saute sausage.
Drain all the grease off.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Layer the cubes of bread, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour liquid mixture on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine gravy, chicken and vegetables in a bowl; set aside. In a pie dish, place a bottom crust.
Dot with a little butter. Pour in chicken and gravy mixture.
Place the other crust over top of pie dish.
Seal and crimp the edges.
Vent top crust with 2 or 3 small slits.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crust looks browned lightly.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Let cool. Cream the cheese and sugar. Add jello. Chill.
Chill milk and whip until creamy. Fold in cheese mixture.

title: fruit goody
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Dice and add bananas when ready to serve.

title: faye's egg nog(mom's recipe)
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks with 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat whites with 1 1/4 cups sugar and whipping cream.
Blend in milk (and whiskey).

title: marinade(great on chicken)
directions: Marinate overnight for best results and baste while grilling.

title: jello cake
directions: Beat all together for 3 minutes.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Grease 2 coffee cans.

title: meatless spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in a wide frying pan over medium heat.
Add onion and chili and cook until onion is soft.
Mix in garlic, tomatoes with their liquid (break up with spoon), tomato sauce, olives, capers and oregano.
Adjust heat so that mixture boils gently.
Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until sauce is slightly thickened (15 to 20 minutes).
Use over spaghetti or any pasta.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop small balls on cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain noodles.
Separately mix ingredients in pan and cook until it gets thick and bubbly, then mix in sharp Cheddar cheese.
Pour mixture in with noodles.
Heat at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: almond rice betel
directions: Melt bark in microwave or in double boiler; add peanut butter and mix.
Fold in Rice Krispies and marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: dink's sweet and sour kielbasi
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, water, pimento and salt over low-medium heat, stirring for 15 minutes.
Blend cold water and cornstarch into hot mixture, stirring over heat until mixture thickens.
Stir in paprika.
Meanwhile cut kielbasi or smoked sausage into 2-inch pieces and bring to boil in water for approximately 10 minutes, drain.
Add to mixture in crockpot. Best served second day after prepared.
Enjoy!

title: stuffed flank steak florentine
directions: Pound each steak with mallet to 1/3-inch thickness; set aside. Combine egg, spinach, cheese, sage, salt and pepper.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Spread mixture over steaks.
Starting from narrow side, roll up jelly roll fashion.
Tie with string.
In large skillet, brown steak rolls in oil on all sides.
Place in a a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan with 1/3 cup milk. Beat egg yolks; add to remaining milk.
Stir well.
Add egg mixture to saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, margarine and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites, adding 1/4 cup sugar and cover pie.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Cook carrots and onions in small amount of salted water; drain.
Break salmon into chunks; place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Add carrots, onions and macaroni.
Stir in soup, salt and pepper.
Melt butter; toss with bread crumbs.
Top with crumbs and cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 20 minutes.
Serve with stewed tomatoes, apple, cherry and nut salad and fruit cobbler dessert.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare the stuffing according to directions.
Combine milk and meat. Divide into 5 patties.
On wax paper, pat each to a 6-inch circle.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each. Draw meat over stuffing and seal.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: garbage chop suey
directions: Brown hamburg; drain off fat.
Saute onions, garlic, pepper, celery and mushrooms (chopped) in a frying pan.
Drain; then mix with browned beef with tomato paste, spaghetti sauce and oregano.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake like cornbread at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl mix oats, flour, sugar and salt.
Pour very hot melted butter over the mixture and stir until sugar has melted.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir well. Refrigerate about 15-20 minutes.
Cover cookie sheets with heavy duty aluminum foil and spray Pam on foil.
Drop 1/4 teaspoonfuls of mixture on foil 2 inches apart.
Cook 10-12 minutes.
Watch carefully.
When completely cool peel off foil.
Small cold balls work best so it may be necessary to refrigerate longer than 15-20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: hot dan's dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat with rotary beater until light and fluffy.
Especially good on potato salad, coleslaw and deviled eggs.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour and mix into a large bowl.
Heat in saucepan, oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Bring to rapid boil. Pour hot over sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 11 x 16-inch jelly roll pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix all of the ingredients together and chill.

title: the "berry-best" muffins
directions: If using frozen fruit, partially thaw and combine with 1/4 cup flour.
Fresh berries should be rinsed, drained and well-dusted with flour before folding into batter.

title: cuban black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight or add 1 teaspoon salt to 6 cups of water and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 3 1/2 to 4 hours. Crush together garlic, salt, cumin, oregano and dry mustard.
Heat oil and saute onions about 5 minutes in a large skillet.
Add green peppers and continue to cook until onions are tender.
Stir in seasoning, lemon juice and 1/2 cup bean liquid.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add to beans.
Cook until flavors blend, about 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut for 15 minutes.
Cut with scissors into 1-inch pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Cover and store for 24 hours.

title: grenadine dressing for slaw
directions: Add vinegar, grenadine and sugar to the mayonnaise until the color and flavor suit the taste.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Dip sliced bananas in lemon juice; set aside.
Combine Eagle Brand milk, water and pudding; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Layer mixture with wafers and bananas.
Chill.

title: aunt hattie's cheesecake
directions: Combine the first three ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving some to top cheesecake.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; let cool until partly set.

title: beef and bean barbecue bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat, drain.
Add pork and beans, barbecue sauce, onion and salt; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 of the cheese, cut into cubes.
Pour into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Cut biscuits in half, forming half circle.
Place cut side down, around edge of casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining Velveeta slices.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: country potato salad
directions: Cut unpeeled tomatoes into quarters.
Place in a boiler with enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes.
Drain potatoes and place in a large bowl and mix with other ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: biscuit topped italian casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Brown beef and onions; drain.
Stir in water, pepper, tomato sauce and paste. Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in thawed vegetables and 1 1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon mixture in baking dish.

title: egg noodle bake casserole
directions: Boil noodles until tender (done); drain and rinse.
(Add salt to water before boiling.)
Brown ground chuck in skillet and drain. Combine tomato paste as you would when making spaghetti sauce. Simmer until medium-thick consistency.
Cream the sour cream and Philadelphia cream cheese in a bowl.
After washing the green onions, cut stems up and stir into the creamy mixture.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix as for pie crust.
Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Makes 4 (3 1/2 x 6-inch) loaves or 3 longer foil pans.
Cream eggs, sugar and oleo.
Add flour and soda; mix well.
Add boiling water; mix, then add walnuts and dates.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar. Combine egg, oil and bananas; add to the dry ingredients.
Mix only to dampen flour.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: chicken and potato casserole
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Parboil for 5 minutes in salted water to cover.
Heat cream of chicken soup with milk.
Add cheese and onion.

title: carrot pie
directions: Combine carrots, eggs, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Add milk and honey, blending until smooth.
Pour filling into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Allow pie to cool.
Garnish with whipped cream or Cool Whip before serving.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: pepper steak oriental
directions: Cut partially frozen beef into diagonal 1/4-inch strips.
In a large bowl, combine soy sauce, 1 tablespoon oil and pepper.
Add beef; toss to coat well; let stand several hours in refrigerator. Drain beef, reserving marinade.
Stir fry until beef is browned, about 4 minutes.
Remove beef with slotted spoon.
Add green peppers, mushrooms and onions to wok.
Cook and stir until vegetables are crisp and tender, about 2 minutes.
Return beef to wok, combine reserved marinade, beef broth and cornstarch, pour over beef mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add tomatoes; cover and cook until heated through, about 2 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Saute bacon until brown.
Add onions and saute until translucent; drain and set aside.
In mixer bowl, combine egg yolk, salt, pepper, mustard, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and dill weed on medium speed.
Slowly add the oil and blend well. Add bacon and onions.
If too thick, thin the dressing with additional vinegar, adjusting seasonings to proportions.
Serve within 30 minutes; do not store.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: olive-rye appetizer
directions: Combine beef, cheese and ripe olives with mayonnaise.
Spread 1 tablespoon of the mixture on each cracker.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese melts. Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: my favorite punch
directions: Chill juices and ginger ale.
Mix juices; stir in sherbet. Add ginger ale last, just before serving.
Serves 50.

title: baked pheasant and rice
directions: Blend mushroom soup and milk.
Combine with rice and onion soup.
Mix and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange pheasant on top.
Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with paprika and bake, uncovered, in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Chicken or quail can be used if pheasant not available.)

title: escole soup
directions: In a large pot, heat broth.
In another pot, boil escole in water until it is tender, drain.
Mix ground chicken with bread crumbs and 1 egg, beaten.
Make into mini meatballs.
Fry with vegetable oil.
In a separate pot, boil pastine.
Add drained escole, pastine and meatballs to broth.
Add 1/2 cup to 1 cup of grated Locatelli cheese.
Once all is added, drop beaten egg into mixture.
Mix all together and let simmer on warm for 5 minutes. Enjoy!

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain. Melt cheese in crock-pot. Add Ro-Tel and sausage. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Sift flour and sugar together 3 times.
Add flour and sour cream alternately to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour into angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cream together sugar, egg yolks and butter.
Add milk and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites beaten fairly stiff, but not dry.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes or until set and golden brown.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small cubes.
This should take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire about 4 weeks at 365°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to find them in their stew.

title: crispy zucchini spears
directions: Combine egg and milk in a small bowl.
In another bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Roll each zucchini spear in egg/milk mixture, then coat well in flour mixture.
Cook in hot oil until crisp and brown.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk to a boil.
Cool for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: mexican hot dip
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion together.
Drain off fat. In crockpot combine all ingredients and heat on low for 2 hours, stirring frequently.
If too thick, add more salsa.
Serve with tortilla chips (can be doubled, for a crowd).

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain well.
Saute onion in oleo; add cheese, milk and soup, stirring until melted and blended together for cheese sauce.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 people.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook celery, onion, garlic salt and salt in water until nearly done (about 15 minutes).
Add chicken and cook 15 minutes longer. Remove from fire and drain.
Save broth and cook spaghetti in it. Add chicken mixture to spaghetti and broth.
Add pimentos, mushrooms and mushroom soup.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: margo's salsa
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a blender or food processor. Mix for 30 seconds or longer, depending on the consistency desired (longer for thin salsa, less for thick salsa). Refrigerate salsa for at least an hour before serving.

title: chinese riblets
directions: You will need a mixing bowl or pan and a baking pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan; pour melted margarine over stuffing mix.
Put cut up chicken in bottom of pan.
Cook soup, milk and broth to a good mixture.
Pour evenly over chicken.
Put stuffing on top of this and barely press into broth.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 7-Up and juices.
Put 7-Up in just before serving.
Chill 7-Up and juices before putting together.

title: low calorie dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend until smooth. Allow to stand for about 15 minutes to develop full flavor.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook rigatoni according to package directions.
Saute pepper strips and onion in oil for 5 minutes.
Put drained pasta in 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Mix in pepper, onion, mushrooms and pepperoni. Spoon sauce over all; sprinkle with Parmesan and top with Mozzarella.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Run under broiler for 1 to 2 minutes until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: mock turtle soup
directions: Add all ingredients, except flour and eggs, and simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Brown the flour.
Make a paste of the flour and an additional 2 to 3 cups of hot water in a blender. Add to the soup.
Chop the hard-boiled eggs and add to soup. Simmer an additional 1 hour.

title: deb's brownies
directions: Melt
shortening and cocoa together.
Remove from heat. Stir in by hand:
sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and nuts. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers in round slices.
Add salt and let set for 2 hours, then drain.
Put vinegar and sugar over cucumbers.
Stir mixture until sugar is dissolved.
Place in containers and freeze.

title: tennessee beef skillet
directions: In a skillet, fry ground beef and onions.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese and corn chips.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over corn chips, then top with cheese.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, cream and water to the softball stage in boiling.
After reaching soft ball stage, remove from heat.
Melt in butter, then add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until ready to pour in a pan or spoon out on a buttered paper or aluminum foil.

title: rainbow jello mold
directions: Preparing each color separately, pour Jell-O into a bowl and add one cup of boiling water; stir until Jell-O is dissolved, then add 1 1/2 cups of cold water.
Stir for a few minutes, until Jell-O is cooled, then pour in 1/2 cup heavy cream.

title: brazil cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually; cream thoroughly until light and fluffy.
Blend in the vanilla.
Add egg yolk; beat well. Sift in flour and salt, mixing until thoroughly blended.
Shape into balls 3/4-inch in diameter.
Dip in unbeaten egg whites; roll lightly in the chopped nuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Make a small depression in each ball with tip of a teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes, or until a delicate brown.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Place a half teaspoon of bright red jelly in each little depression.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mary's onion casserole
directions: Put a layer of sliced onions in bottom of a casserole serving 4 people.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add 8 small nobs of butter around each layer of onions.
Repeat until casserole is full.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350° without removing cover.

title: squash puffs
directions: Boil squash, drain and mash.
Should have approximately 1 cup of squash.
Combine squash with Egg Beaters and mix well.
Combine flour, corn meal and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add to squash mixture with onion and season with salt substitute of your choice. Drop into lightly oiled pan.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Drain.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook vegetables and garlic until tender.
Stir in pasta sauce and oregano; simmer 15 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and Parmesan in a bowl.
In a 13 x 9-inch dish, layer 1/2 each of the noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Parmesan mixture, plus 1/2 of Mozzarella.
Repeat layering and cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover for 15 minutes more.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour beans in baking pan.
Add the juice from the pineapple and 1/2 of the crushed pineapple.
Blend mustard, barbecue sauce and brown sugar; mix well with the beans, pineapple and pineapple juice.
Bake in oven at 350°, uncovered, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: cold night chili
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery.
Add hamburger and brown. Drain away grease.
Add beans, chiles, tomato paste, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and chili powder to taste.
Let simmer until dinner time.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine and combine all ingredients.
Stir with a spoon. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: crisp jumbo chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream butter well and gradually beat in sugar until mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Chill dough 30 minutes or until firm enough to handle.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix on top of soups, then drizzle chicken broth with melted margarine over stuffing.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.
Don't overcook or topping will be hard.

title: peach waffle cake
directions: Toast waffles and spread 1 teaspoon of butter over each.
In small bowl, combine peach slices with preserves and cinnamon. Spoon peach mixture over 1 waffle.
Place other waffle on top of peaches and top with whipped cream.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion, pepper and meat.
Add to tomatoes and rice. Place in casserole.
Bake slowly for 1 hour at 325°.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Place all other ingredients in mixing bowl and stir in the yeast mixture until well mixed.
Turn onto floured surface and knead dough.
Roll into biscuits.
Bake at 450° until done.
Dough may be covered and stored in refrigerator 2 or 3 days.

title: cauliflower cajun style
directions: Place
cauliflower
in a shallow baking dish.
Add salt and pepper
to tomatoes; boil rapidly until most of liquid has evaporated.
Pour
over
cauliflower.
Top	with
cheese, then crumbs.
Dot
with	butter	or margarine.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 15 minutes, long enough to get piping hot.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Use 2 loaves of frozen bread dough.
Thaw and break up 1 loaf; put in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put filling in.
Break up other loaf of bread dough and put over filling.
Let it rise. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. Add remaining ingredients. Store at room temperature in a 1-gallon covered container in a warm, draft free place for 3 to 4 days, stirring 2 or 3 times a day. Cover during night; uncover during day. Then store in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.

title: chicken adobo(a filipino dish)
directions: Put all ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for at least 1 hour.
Serve over rice or thin noodles.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix in bowl, jello, Kool-aid and sugar.
Add boiling water and stir well until dissolved.
Add cold water and mix well.
Pour into 3 ounce Dixie cups.
Place in freezer for about 1 1/2 hours, until starting to set.
Place popsicle sticks in center when they will stand up.
When ready to eat, hold in warm hand for a while and slip popsicle out of cup.

title: ham-aghetti casserole(microwave)
directions: With scissors, snip bacon into 1-inch pieces in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High 4 to 5 minutes; remove half the fat. Add ham, tomatoes, spaghetti, onion, green peppers, salt and pepper.
Microwave at High 18 to 20 minutes, until spaghetti is tender, stirring after 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes, uncovered, until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stir in flour and nuts. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Allow to cool.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix all of the above and add red and green seedless grapes you can add nuts if you want. This salad will hold well.

title: quick lamb casserole
directions: Cut or form lamb into patties.
Brown lightly.
Pour off excess fat.
Put into large Dutch oven or casserole.
Dissolve soup in boiled water.
Pour over lamb and bring again to a boil. Add rice; bring to boil again.
Cover and bake in a 400° oven for about 40 minutes or until rice is cooked and water is absorbed. Serves 6.

title: welsh rarebit with tomatoes and bacon
directions: Place bacon on microwavable rack in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish; cover with paper towels. Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes. Drain on paper towels; crumble and set aside.

title: easy lemon chess pie
directions: Put everything in a food processor or blender.
Blend well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 360° for 45 to 50 minutes. Refrigerate.
Best served cold.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Marinate wings in mixture for at least 2 hours in refrigerator, turning once.
Wings can marinate overnight.
Place wings on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, turning and basting with reserved marinade.
Crisp under broiler or put on grill to brown.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix pudding, uncooked, with the cans of pineapple, including the juice.
Add marshmallows and whipped topping.
Stir well. Refrigerate for 2 hours and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except olives
with mixer.	Fold in olives.
Shape into a ball.
Chill until serving.

title: one minute fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, being careful not to let it burn you.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until it cools and starts getting thick.
Spread on aluminum foil; slice when cool.

title: friday fish any day of the week
directions: Batter fish pieces in 12-inch skillet.
Pour in cooking oil, let oil get hot on medium fire.
Fry for 5 minutes, turning on both sides until golden brown or batter pieces, use just enough oil to prevent from sticking, about 1 tablespoon in a baking pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, turning over once until golden brown.

title: maple-nut angel food cake
directions: Make batter for angel food cake as directed, except add 1 teaspoon maple flavoring during last 1/2 minute of mixing.
Fold in 1/3 cup finely chopped pecans.
Bake as directed.
Cool.
Serve wedges with ice cream and Caramel Sauce.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash pork chops; pat dry and sprinkle with Season-All salt.
Wash and slice potatoes.
Layer in a well-greased baking pan.
Top with pork chops, salt, pepper and onion and one teaspoon of butter in four corners of pan.
Cover and bake until potatoes are done.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken until 1/2-inch thick.
Place a slice of ham and cheese on each piece of chicken.
Roll up carefully, beginning at narrow end; secure rolls with wooden picks.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and allspice.
Coat rolls with flour mixture.
Dip rolls into egg, then roll in bread crumbs.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown rolls, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and add water. Cover; simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove cover last 2 to 3 minutes to crisp rolls slightly.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Puree all ingredients in blender until smooth.
0 Fat!!!!! 163 calories.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and milk; stir well.
Spoon over chicken; sprinkle stuffing on top.
Drizzle butter over crumbs. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Blend together on medium speed the oil, brown sugar and eggs until creamy.
Sift and add together with oil mixture the flour, baking powder and salt.
(Mixture will be very stiff and sticky.) Then add chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: honey oatmeal bread
directions: Combine milk, honey, oil and salt in a saucepan; heat to 115°. Set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add milk mixture, oats and two cups flour; mix well.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place each of the ingredients in an oblong dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch) in the order they are listed.
(This may be prepared a day or two ahead of time.)
Do not mix until ready to serve.

title: weight watchers meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and place into 2 loaves.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
(Is 4% protein, 1 bread exchange and 10 optional calories.)

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for several hours before serving.

title: jam cake
directions: Sift flour once, then measure.
Add dry ingredients; sift 3 times.
Cream sugar and shortening well.
Add eggs, milk, jam and raisins.
Mix lightly and pour in two 9-inch square pans.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: falling in love cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together,
except
chocolate
and nuts. Beat 4 minutes
at
medium speed; stir in chocolate and nuts. Bake in oblong pan
(greased) or tube pan at 350° about 40 minutes or until a
toothpick comes out clean.
Let rest 10 minutes. Frost when cool.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: In a large saucepan on medium heat, warm milk.
Add chips and vanilla.
Stir till melted; cook one minute.
Spread in buttered dish (small).
Let set in cool place.
Cut in small squares.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until it comes off bone.
Mix stuffing with butter.
In baking dish, put 1/2 of stuffing, chicken, salt and pepper to taste.
Then spread over this cream of chicken, mushroom, celery soup in that order.
Do not mix.
Pour broth over mix.
Put remaining stuffing on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Check after 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Slightly brown meat and drain on paper towels.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir in bread, meat and cheese. Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: mexican chip casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, and garlic until onion is tender, drain. Add soup, corn and chillies. In 13 x 9 pan layer meat mixture, corn chips and enchilada sauce, top with cheese.

title: not yo mamma's brownies
