directions: Over low heat, melt chocolate chips and butter.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until bars pull away from sides (do not overcook).
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars. May use vanilla chips or brickle chips in place of peanut butter chips.

title: zucchini quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Set aside.

title: oven pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix until well combined. Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. (It puffs way up as it bakes and falls when you remove it from oven.)
Cut into squares and serve with butter, syrup and fresh fruit (strawberries are great).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; cool.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple, lemon juice, celery and walnuts.
Chill the cranberry sauce and pineapple before starting; your salad will set more quickly.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set overnight.

title: grandma hampton's whiskey cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Divide dough in half and pat in a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Beat egg white on a flat plate with a fork until frothy.
Brush on dough and sprinkle with nuts; sprinkle with cinnamon if desired.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375° or until edges brown.
Cool slightly and cut into squares or triangles.

title: picante chicken
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in a large saucepan for about 4 minutes.
Stir in chicken; cook until no longer pink.
Sprinkle sage and salt over chicken; cook and stir 1 minute.
Stir in picante sauce, beans, vermouth and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in peppers and tomato; simmer for 10 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Serve in bowl.
Top with shredded cheese and sour cream.
Serve with chips.

title: maple white chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars and extract until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs. Sift flour, soda and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixture. Mix until well blended. Fold in white chips (nuts). Spoon out by teaspoon or larger spoon. Bake at 375° around 10 minutes until lightly browned or darker if you like crispy.

title: onion custard
directions: Simmer diced onions in melted margarine until golden, but not brown.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings, then add onion mixture. Bake in a greased 1-quart casserole in a 375° oven for about 25 minutes or until custard is set.
Serve hot.

title: easy beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Add
salt	and
pepper
to taste.	Add cream of mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with Tater Tots. Cook for 25
minutes
Add grated cheese to top of casserole.	Cook until cheese is melted.

title: beef nacho casserole(35 minutes)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Brown meat; drain. Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder. Put 1/2 of meat mixture in 2-quart casserole. Put 1 cup crushed chips on top of meat in dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of each cheese on top of chips, then add rest of meat, rest of chips and rest of each cheese to make layers. Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Top with lettuce and tomato if desired. Serves 6.

title: christmas egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add milks.
Blend in vanilla.
Beat egg whites to form peaks.
Fold in whites and whiskey.
Chill! Add red cake coloring to give holiday look!
Top with whipped cream.

title: miniature pecan tarts
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and 1/2 cup margarine.
Stir in flour and chill for 1 hour.
Mix together the egg, brown sugar, 1 tablespoon margarine and vanilla.
Put small ball of dough in small muffin pan; press dough against sides of muffin pan.
Fill with spoonful of pecan mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: shipwreck
directions: Layer potatoes, then onions, then ground beef.
Add the kidney beans.
Repeat with potatoes, onions and beef.
Add the tomato soup and 1/2 can water.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done, about 2 hours.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef with bacon.
Add onion; cook until tender, but not brown.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in soup and cook slowly, uncovered 15-20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cool and then stir in sour cream and re-heat.
DO NOT BOIL.
Note:
Sour cream will not curdle if mixture is cool.
Serve over rice.

title: old fashioned egg pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, then turn oven temperature to 350° and bake until set. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate amaretto cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, cottage cheese, cocoa, flour, almond extract and salt.
Beat in egg until
blended.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes. Check for doneness.
Chill. Yield: 12 servings (200 calories per serving).

title: no-bake peanutty drops
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, bring to boil the sugar and corn syrup; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and fold in remaining ingredients until well blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool until firm.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In large saucepan, cook sugar, syrup and water until it reaches hard ball stage when dropped in a cup of cool water.
Add peanuts and cook until golden brown.
Add butter and vanilla. Stir until well mixed.
Add soda and stir well.
Do not stir too long after adding soda.
(This is the secret of this candy.)
Pour onto buttered pan or wax paper.
Let cool and break into pieces. Makes 2 pounds.

title: crock-pot scalloped potatoes
directions: Lightly grease the crock-pot.
Stir together the butter, onions, potatoes, cream of mushroom soup, milk, cheese, green pepper, black pepper and 1/2 the cracker crumbs.
Transfer to the crock-pot and top with remaining crumbs.
Cover and cook on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: cool 'n easy fruited pie
directions: In large bowl stir boiling water into jell-o until dissolved. Add ice cubes to cold water to equal 1-1/4 c., and add to the jell-o.
Stir until slightly thickened and remove remaining ice. Stir in Cool Whip until smooth.
Stir in fruit.
Refrigerate 20-30 minutes until mixture is thick and will form mounds.
Spoon into crust and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: dan's favorite herbed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes but do not peel them.
Quarter.
In a large pot of boiling water, boil the potatoes for 10 to 15 minutes, or until tender when pierced with a fork.
Drain and coarsely mash the potatoes with the butter, half and half, 1 1/4 cups of the cheese, chives and nutmeg.
Season to taste.
Spread potatoes evenly in a buttered 8 x 10-inch or oval baking dish.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top and heat for 15 minutes in a preheated 350° oven. Brown the top under a broiler and serve.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Cook carrots until tender.
Drain both well.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Gradually stir in flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook until smooth.
In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange half of the noodles, top with half of the carrots, ham, cheese, parsley, onion and milk mixture.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey bake ole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 2-quart casserole and bottom of large skillet with nonstick cooking spray until well coated.
Heat skillet over medium-high heat, about 30 seconds.
Crumble ground turkey into skillet; add onion.
Cook and stir 3 to 5 minutes or until turkey is lightly browned.
Stir in taco sauce, tomato sauce, green chilies and cumin; blend well.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread meat in casserole (8-inch or 1 1/2-quart) on bottom. Add onion on top of meat.
Spread soup next.
Add layer of Tater Tots in single layer on top.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Enjoy!!!

title: soft gallets(belgian cookie waffle)
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy (fold into batter last). Blend white and brown sugar, softened butter and Crisco. Cream well. Add yolks and blend. Add vanilla. Add flour and cream alternating. Fold in egg whites. Bake in waffle iron, rounded teaspoonful for each waffle. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Keeps well in airtight tin with waxed paper between layers of waffles.

title: caramel dip
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan melt butter and caramels over low heat (12 to 15 minutes).
Stir in pecans, milk and rum extract. Keep warm in crock-pot or fondue.
Use as a dip for wedges of apples, pears, oranges and bananas.
To reheat, add 1 to 2 tablespoons of milk; heat slowly.
Yields:
1 1/2 cups.

title: tuna ball
directions: *Can use 1/2 teaspoon dried minced onions.

title: apple cake
directions: Step 1:
Sift together first 4 ingredients and set aside.

title: no eggs ice cream
directions: Combine pudding and milk.
Beat until well blended.
Add vanilla.
Put pudding in ice cream freezer.
Add sugar and fill freezer up with milk.
Any fruits can be added to pudding.
It's real good.

title: easy pizza pie
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and spices until meat is done.
(Dice up onion in meat.)
Spread 1 can of crescent rolls on bottom of a loaf pan.
Spread tomato soup (or tomato sauce) on crescent rolls. Spread beef mixture over that, then cheese soup (or shredded Cheddar cheese).
Top with other can of rolls and bake until as brown as you like.

title: mini birthday hamburgers and hot dogs
directions: Broil or boil hot dogs.
Serve on finger rolls.
Form ground beef into 2-inch patties and broil.
Place on small round rolls. Serve with usual condiments.
For added fun, serve with mini milk shakes in juice glasses.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Beat thoroughly while pouring a pint of Wesson oil into it. This is good homemade mayonnaise.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Cook onions in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Combine meat and seasoning; beat in egg and mix thoroughly.
Beat in cream.
Form mixture into 1-inch balls.
Lightly brown in butter or margarine.
Remove excess fat.
Add consomme.
Cook uncovered 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken fantastic
directions: Combine soup, preserves and salad dressing.
Arrange chicken in a 12 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Brush with oil; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Cover with waxed paper. Microwave on Medium-high for 12 to 15 minutes, or until chicken is done.

title: mom's chicken and vegetables
directions: Fry the chicken until completely cooked (crispy).
In separate pan add: green pepper, celery, onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste and crushed tomatoes.
Stew until tender (30 minutes).
Pour vegetables over chicken in frying skillet, simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: oriental smoked chicken
directions: Salt chicken inside and out; place in a heavy plastic bag. Refrigerate 5 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine; stir in flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place potatoes and onion in baking dish; pour in sauce.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mashed party potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; blend sour cream and cream cheese.
Add to cooked potatoes and mash.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put into greased casserole dish; brush with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven until hot.
(Can be made the day before and heated when ready to eat.)

title: ham roll-ups
directions: You will need colored toothpicks.

title: chicken milano(an easy make-ahead casserole)
directions: Saute chicken, onion, celery and pepper in 2 tablespoons oil for about 4 minutes.
Add mushrooms and seasonings and simmer 20 minutes.
Blend in soup and milk and cook 5 minutes.
Cook linguine according to package directions and toss with chicken mixture.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Overlap tomato slices on top.
Toss croutons with butter and spread over tomatoes.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake another 10 minutes.

title: oreo cookies
directions: Mix together cake mixes, shortening and eggs.
Form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.
When cool, fill.

title: viva italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed and add all other ingredients. Refrigerate.
May add olives, celery, peppers, ham cubes, cheese cubes, etc.

title: low-cal stuffing for fish
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Stuff your fish.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into pieces and cook in boiling water until tender; drain.
Boil and debone chicken.
Combine chicken, pimento, green pepper and onion in a casserole dish.
Mix soup with broth from boiled chicken and add to chicken mixture.
Add cheese and spaghetti; season to taste.
Toss lightly until well blended.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cracklin' cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased iron skillet.
Bake at 425° until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage.
Remove sausage with slotted spoon to a large mixing bowl.
In skillet saute celery, onion, pepper and garlic.
Dump into bowl with sausage.
Blend in 1 can broth, 1 can soup, 1 can broth and 1 can soup.
Stir in mushrooms, chestnuts and thyme.
Mix in packet of spices from Uncle Ben's box; blend in rice.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fried deer chops
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with mixture. Brown on both sides in shortening in large skillet.
When meat is well browned, add water.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes until tender.
Remove chops to heated platter.
Prepare milk gravy. Serve gravy with chops.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: *Can use 1 1/4 teaspoons cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon each of nutmeg, ginger and 1/4 teaspoon cloves.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream brown sugar, oil and eggs, beating well after each egg addition.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Combine with creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips.
The dough will be very heavy.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares when partially cooled.

title: stove top beef
directions: Put oil in 6-quart pot.
Place onions on the floor of the pot. Put the beef over the raw onions.
The beef could be frozen.
Add the seasonings, garlic cloves, Bovril and pepper.
Put on very low fire; simmer for a couple of hours.
Keep cover on.

title: apricot bread
directions: Cover apricots with warm water and soak for 30 minutes. Drain and cut with scissors into 1/4 inch pieces. Mix together sugar, butter and egg. Stir in water and orange juice. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and blend in. Add nuts and apricots. Pour into glass bread pan. Let stand for about 20 minutes. Bake at 350 degrees for about an hour.

title: brown sugar divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup.
Slowly bring to a boil and cook until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Beat egg whites with the cream of tartar.
Slowly add syrup and beat until firm.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: lemon curd bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter ("I do it in the microwave").
Add flour and powdered sugar.
Mix well and press into the bottom of a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
There is no need to have the crust come up the sides.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: holiday ham ball
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet; mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Immediately remove from pan and serve warm.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan or glass baking dish with Pam.
Combine all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Pour into dish. Crush crackers and toss with butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over vegetables.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pull aparts
directions: Open tubes of biscuits.
Separate and cut each into four pieces.
Roll each piece in sugar and cinnamon.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan, keeping tightly packed.
Melt butter; add brown sugar and ice cream.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: ham and asparagus parmesan
directions: Cook and slice ham. Boil asparagus for a few minutes.
Layer ham on bottom of greased pan.
Layer asparagus over ham.
Pour over butter and sprinkle with cheese, pepper and salt.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for about 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: waldorf style salad
directions: Combine apple with the lemon juice, sweetener, vinegar, dry mustard and paprika.
Make sure that apple is coated with lemon juice which will prevent browning.
Toss in celery.
Good accompaniment to cottage cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender; drain off liquid and mash.
Beat together eggs and milk; add to squash.
Mix cheese, margarine and cracker crumbs.
Add 1/2 of this to squash mixture; pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh fruit shell salad
directions: Cook pasta to desired doneness.
Drain and set aside.
In a small bowl, mix the yogurt and orange juice concentrate.
In a large bowl, combine the fruit.
Add the yogurt mixture and pasta; toss to coat.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Toss gently before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream
together shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.	Add all other ingredients and blend well.
Drop level teaspoon of dough onto greased cookie sheet. Press
cookies
lightly
with fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: complete meal
directions: Open a box of your favorite frozen fried chicken; follow directions on box.
Open 3 cans of your favorite canned vegetables. Put each can in separate bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon butter to each bowl. Put vegetables in microwave.
Cook according to directions.
When microwave beeps, remove vegetables; place on table.
Have 1 large can of fruit, already opened and chilled.
When chicken and vegetables are done, put all food on table including bought rolls and chilled fruit.
Holler "Come and get it."
When family gets to the table, ask "God's Blessing."
Eat; be merry.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Cut candied fruits in small pieces. Cream butter and sugar until thoroughly blended. Add well beaten egg yolks to butter and sugar mixture. When well mixed, add the whites which have been well beaten. Sift, one half the flour over the fruit. Mix fruit, nuts,
and
1 c. flour in a separate bowl and set aside. Cover the pans with several thickness of waxed paper so the tops of the cake will be kept dry.

title: heavenly pecan pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar until creamy. Put in pie crust and refrigerate. Melt margarine. Add nuts and coconut. Cook until brown or slightly toasted. Cool and cover top of pies with pecan mixture. Drizzle caramel topping over pies. Keep refrigerated.

title: golden twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut lengthwise.
Scoop out potato, leaving 1/8-inch shell. Combine potato, 1 cup cheese, salad dressing, milk, egg and seasonings.
Beat well until fluffy.
Fill shells.
Top with remaining cheese, onion and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until hot.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Beat oranges, oil and eggs until oranges are mashed up. Gradually add cake mix, stirring well until blended.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°.
Frost with icing.
Keep in refrigerator.
Good when baked the day before serving.

title: home brew(jogging in a jug)
directions: Mix and drink 2 ounces daily with supper or before bedtime. Helps you to sleep sound and relieves sore joints and pain.
Also helps digestive system; some call this a cure-all.
You may want to consume this twice a day at the beginning.

title: watergate (pistachio) salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix with pineapple in medium-large bowl.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well and chill before serving. Keep refrigerated.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Pour water into mixing bowl; add flour, cake mix and peanut butter.
Mix on low speed with flat paddle for 2 minutes or until well combined.
Scrape bowl and paddle several times while mixing. Using a #40 scoop, portion batter onto greased sheet pan 1 1/2 inches apart.
Flatten with tines of a fork.
Dip scoop in hot water occasionally to prevent sticking.
Bake in 375° oven for approximately 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store covered.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen or 40 scoops.

title: lynn's vegetable pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly oil 10-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Cook broccoli until almost tender and drain.
Toss together first 4 ingredients and put in pie plate.
Put remaining ingredients in blender and whirl until smooth.
Pour over vegetables in dish.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cool grilled chicken salad
directions: Rinse chicken and place in resealable plastic bag.
In small bowl, combine lemon juice, oil, tarragon and garlic salt.
Blend well.
Pour marinade over chicken.
Seal bag and refrigerate 30 to 45 minutes or overnight.
Drain chicken; reserve marinade.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and then blend this with the egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Divide batter into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Roll out one package of dough in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together at high speed the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Spread over dough in pan.
Cut remaining dough into 1/4-inch slices and place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add onions and cook about 3 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, tomato juice, chili powder, beans, potatoes and garlic.
Cook covered about 2 hours.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add Texas Pete.

title: cake icing
directions: Mix until combined and then whip it until white.

title: fruit dip
directions: Use equal parts of marshmallow cream and Cool Whip.
Mix with electric mixer.
Dip fruits of your choice.

title: green lima bean casserole
directions: Boil lima beans and whole onion until beans are tender. Drain; chop onion and return to beans.
Add green pepper, celery and tomato sauce.
Mix and pour into casserole.
Top with raw bacon slices.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, watching that bacon does not burn.
Serves 4 (can be doubled).

title: "more!" casserole
directions: Combine all in large casserole.
Mix well.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry ribbon salad
directions: Mix boiling water and Jell-O.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Pour half of mixture into dish, let set until firm and then spread with 1 carton sour cream.
Add remaining Jell-O mixture.
Let set until firm.

title: old-fashion meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
If too moist, add more crackers until you are able to pat into loaf and remains together. Place in baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes on lower rack.
Remove from oven and drain 1/2 of drippings from dish.
Spread about 1/2 cup of ketchup on the top of the meat loaf and return to the oven and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Check meat loaf by slicing and removing middle slice.
If red in middle return to oven for additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: health bread
directions: Boil water and raisins together for 5 minutes; cool.
Mix together all other ingredients; pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add peppers and onion, cook until brown.
Add tomato sauce, water, sugar, salt and peppers; simmer 5 minutes.
Add rice, mix well. Pour into well-greased casserole. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until top bubbles.

title: crock-pot venison stew
directions: Salt and pepper meat and roll in flour.
Brown in cooking oil on all sides.
Place vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Prepare the dry soup mix according to package directions and pour in pot. Add 2 more cups of water.
Put browned venison on top of all and cook for 4 to 5 hours on high.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: oat-chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars with softened butter (oleo).
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips or raisins.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.

title: butter rich brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small, heavy saucepan, melt the chocolate and 1 stick of butter over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Cool completely.
In a large bowl with electric mixer, cream together remaining 1 stick of butter and the sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and the chocolate mixture.
Add the flour and a pinch of salt, stirring until mixture is blended well.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into buttered and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, smoothing top. Bake in preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until pulls away slightly from sides of pan.
Serves 12.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bring chicken breasts, garlic powder, salt and pepper to a boil and reduce heat to simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cook vegetables per directions on package.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix margarine with crumbs and press into bottom of a 7-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Into blender, add cream cheese and next 8 ingredients, blending until smooth.
Fold in chocolate morsels.
Slowly pour mixture over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes or until set.
Let cool in pan.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Garnish with chocolate curls, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the butter; add sugar and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating to blend after each addition.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Gradually add flour mixture to butter-sugar-egg mixture; beat continuously.
Blend in sour cream.
Add flavors, one at a time, and blend well.
Turn batter into greased pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until cake springs up to touch.

title: lobster quiche
directions: Line pie shell with cheese slices.
Layer lobster over cheese. Combine cream, eggs, seasonings and flour in bowl; mix well with wire whisk.
Add butter and sherry.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until top is brown and center is set.
Let stand for 20 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs together. Blend well. Add milk, butter, coconut and vanilla. Mix well and pour into 2 well-greased pie pans. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: special ground beef casserole
directions: Cook onions and green pepper in butter in large frypan until onions are transparent.
Add beef; stir until browned.
Add soup, catsup, salt and pepper; simmer for 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend milk, cream cheese and lemon juice; add garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add cream cheese mixture to noodles. Spread noodle mixture in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour beef sauce on top; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Add few nuts.
Mix together and chill for 24 hours.

title: southwestern bean dip
directions: In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain. Transfer to a bowl; add the onion. Mash with a fork until crumbly; set aside. In a blender or food processor, process the tomato sauce and beans until chunky. Add to beef mixture and mix well. Spoon 1/2 into a greased 9 x 13 x 2 inch baking dish. Top with 1/2 of the cheese. Repeat layers. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes, or until cheese is melted. Serve hot with chips.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa and soda.
Then mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp special(serves 1)
directions: Coat pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Saute green onions and peppers until tender.
Add shrimp; let simmer until shrimp turns red.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over shrimp and simmer until mixture thickens.

title: oyster cracker munchies
directions: Put crackers in a plastic bag.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over crackers.
Shake bag to coat crackers; let stand several hours or overnight.
Store in airtight container.

title: pistachio nut torte
directions: Mix wet ingredients, except syrup.
Add cake mix and pudding. Beat 3 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Add chocolate to other half of batter; mix.
Pour over first half and bake one hour at 350°.
Poke holes in cake and pour thin frosting over it.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: popovers with cheese
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Generously grease 6 (5 ounce) custard cups.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in flour, milk and salt just until smooth (do not overbeat).
Fill custard cups about 1/2 full. Sprinkle top of batter with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes. Decrease oven temperature to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer. Immediately remove from cups and serve.
Yields 6 popovers.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, melted margarine and graham crackers; press into pan.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook meat and onion for 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients, mix well and simmer slowly for 45 minutes, partially covered.

title: chicken in sherry
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until chicken is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruited chicken
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; reserve liquid.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to directions, except use reserved liquid as part of required water (I also omit the butter; lower fat, 1/2 calories).
Mix 1/2 of the fruit into the stuffing.
Place stuffing in an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with chicken breast.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes.
Top chicken with remaining fruit.
Bake another 5 to 10 minutes until fruit is hot. (Low-fat, low calorie.)

title: easy frozen delight
directions: Line an 8 x 8-inch glass pan with cream.
Then layer strawberries.
Next, top with crushed vanilla wafers.
Repeat layers until pan is full.
Freeze one hour.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: hamburger and rice
directions: Brown beef in butter and stir in rice.
Add chopped onion to tomatoes and cook while beef is browning, also salt and sugar. Cover, after putting all together, and simmer for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add more water.

title: spanish salad
directions: Clean tomatoes, peppers and onion. Cut up each. Salt and pepper to taste. Toss. Use vinegar and oil as dressing to taste.

title: apple pie
directions: Top with a few patty size pieces of butter. Bake at 425° until fork goes through apples easily.

title: lentil soup
directions: Combine in large pan.
Bring to a boil and cook until done.

title: iced salad
directions: Break head of lettuce in large salad bowl (a clear glass bowl or baking dish is attractive!).
Add in layers:
celery, green pepper and green onions, all chopped.
Add can of tiny English peas (drained), then can of water chestnuts (drained), if desired. Cover this with a layer of mayonnaise, about 2 cups that has been whipped to spreading consistency.
Cover this with a layer of grated Parmesan (in can) cheese.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar, if desired.
Cover with Saran Wrap and let set in refrigerator overnight or at least several hours.
Before serving, add bacon bits on top.
Toss salad gently and serve.
Tantalizes the taste buds!

title: beef parmesan
directions: Shape meat into patties, flour on both sides and fry in enough oil to brown.
When patties are brown, place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover the meat with the spaghetti sauce; spread Mozzarella on top, then sprinkle the Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Use paprika for color.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken pieces, brown and set aside.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; cook until onion is tender.
Force Italian plum tomatoes through a strainer.
Add tomato liquid, parsley, oregano, thyme, salt and pepper to skillet.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: blueberry angel food cake roll
directions: Prepare cake by directions on box, then line 2 cookie sheet pans with aluminum foil.
Divide cake mixture equally into pans. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Invert onto towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
While cake is still warm, roll up into a roll. When cake is cooled, unroll and fill with blueberry pie filling. Roll back up.
This can be topped with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese with 1 cup sugar with a fork.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat with electric mixer until it turns white.
Fill the cupcakes 2/3 full.
Use foil cupcake papers in muffin pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°.
Cool 5 minutes.
Mix sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Spoon on top of center of cupcakes, then drop a teaspoon of strawberry preserves or jelly on top of center.
Comstock canned pie fillings may be used instead of preserves or jelly.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes.
Let cool, then put in refrigerator.
Makes 24 cupcakes.

title: apricot brandy pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix sour cream with all flavoring and apricot brandy. Add flour mixture and sour cream mixture alternately to butter mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan at 325° until a toothpick comes out clean (1 to 1 1/4 hours).

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch tube pan; dust pan with flour.
Cream butter in bowl.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder together into separate bowl.
Alternately add flour mixture and chocolate syrup to butter mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Turn pan upside down on wire rack. Cool cake in pan.
This moist cake needs no frosting.

title: glaze for cakes
directions: Bring to a boil. Boil until it begins to thicken. Add coconut or flavoring.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add soup, green chilies, taco sauce and tomatoes with green chilies.
Put in casserole dish; top with chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill.

title: taco salad
directions: Break up lettuce, cheese and nacho chips.
Mix together.
Cut up tomato into small wedges.
Top with dressing.
Put tomato and dressing in just before serving.

title: dorine's world famous wonderful meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tarter until fluffy. Gradually add sugar and vanilla, beating until stiff and glossy. Spoon onto pie. Bake in 400° oven until golden brown (approximately 10 minutes).

title: caramel melts
directions: Mix cream cheese, 2 sticks oleo and flour.
Shape into small muffin tins and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: artichoke nibble appetizer(real good!)
directions: Drain a can of jalapeno chiles.
Cut lengthwise.
Remove veins, seeds and stems.
Stuff halves with any of the following:

title: celery almondine
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water; set aside.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter over low heat.
Add almonds and saute until golden brown.
Set aside.

title: three cheers ice cream
directions: Add the bananas, sugar and cream to the oranges and lemons. Mix all together and pour into freezer can; finish filling can with milk. Makes 1 gallon.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Put sliced apples in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Blend flour, oats, cinnamon, nutmeg, butter and brown sugar together until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° until topping is golden brown.
Put a great big blop of ice cream on top when you serve it.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies, reserving 1/2 cup.
Press remaining cookies into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle melted margarine over the crushed cookies.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Place cream cheese and confectioners sugar into a deep bowl.
Mix at medium speed until creamy.
Blend in 1 container Cool Whip.
Spread over cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Prepare pudding with 3 1/2 cups cold milk; spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: dole ambrosia
directions: Drain
pineapple and oranges.
Combine remaining ingredients. Fold in yogurt and chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage in very thin strands.
Sprinkle evenly with vinegar, minced onion, fresh ground black pepper and sugar.
Put into airtight bowl or plastic bag and refrigerate for 1 hour or more.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, dry mustard and salt.
Add peppers to sour cream mixture.
Add celery seed at this time.
Add this mixture to chilled cabbage and shake in plastic bags or stir gently to mix thoroughly.
Place back in refrigerator for 2 hours or more.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 10 g, protein 2 g, fat 10 g, calories 130.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix cold milk, orange juice and sour cream and fold into fruit.

title: finnish kropsu(baked pancake)
directions: Put all ingredients except butter into a bowl.
Beat with a rotary beater or an electric mixer.
Batter will be very thin. Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
When butter is melted, add about half of it to batter, leaving remaining butter in pan.
Pour batter over hot butter in pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Will puff up while baking.
Good served with syrup, jam, jelly or honey.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat marshmallows and milk in heavy pan and stir until melted. Pour over Jell-O and stir until dissolved, then add cream cheese and beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in pineapple and let cool.
Blend in Dream Whip and nuts and refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Boil vegetables and drain.
Mix all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Sprinkle crackers and vegetables in casserole dish, then slice butter on top of crackers and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in cherries and nuts.
(Don't chop nuts or cherries.)
Bake in floured and greased tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Test with toothpick before removing from oven.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend in blender and serve immediately.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients by hand (do not use mixer).
Fold in 1 large Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: broccoli lasagna
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, heat soup and broccoli until broccoli is thawed, then in skillet, in 1 tablespoon oil, cook carrots and onion until lightly browned.
Reduce heat; stir in 1/4 cup water. Simmer for 15 minutes, covered, until vegetables are very tender; remove to a bowl.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease a 13 X 9 X 2 inch pan. Combine all ingredients, mix.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour. Recipe can be halved easily.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spread pie filling evenly over 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle pineapple over pie filling, then the dry cake mix. Top with coconut and nuts. Cover with foil; bake 20 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: super sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain off fat and add hot dogs. Add remaining ingredients except cheese and buns. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Spoon onto toasted hamburger bun bottoms.
Top with cheese. Place under broiler until cheese is melted. Replace top half of bun and serve.

title: flank steak marinated
directions: Make marinade in plastic bag with soy sauce, water, onion flakes and parsley.
Add scored steak to bag.
Secure and marinate in refrigerator at least 2 hours, turning once or twice.
Broil on hot grill.

title: devilicious cherry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Drain cherries, reserving syrup.
In saucepan, blend 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch; gradually add cherry syrup, mixing well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat; stir in wine and cherries.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, milk and vanilla until fluffy.
Cut cake in squares.
Top each square with a mound of cream cheese mixture.
Serve warm cherry sauce over all.

title: punch red
directions: Use all sweetened juices or add some sugar.
Use cherry Kool-Aid to get right color of red, using a little at a time until you reach desired color.

title: kielbasa and cabbage
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; set aside.
Add next 7 ingredients to bacon drippings and cook 10 minutes over medium heat.
Turn cabbage once.
Add sausage; cover and cook another 5 minutes or until sausage is heated.
Sprinkle bacon in and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Alternate flour and apples.
Add pecans last.
Pour into greased pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix yeast and 1/4 cup warm water.
Put shortening in large bowl.
Add sugar and hot water; stir until shortening is melted. Add yeast and egg.
Blend in flour and place in refrigerator. Will keep 3 to 4 days.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soup, water and onion.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or small roaster.
Skin chicken; rinse and roll in dry onion soup mix.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
This serves a lot of folks!
Easy and very good.
Some friends have substituted the chicken with pork chops with good results.

title: five-minute sopaipillas
directions: This is an excellent, easy dessert with many variations.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg, flour, baking soda and vanilla.
The dough is quite soft so may chill, then make into rolls; about two rolls.
Slice rolls thin and dip one side of cookie into nutmeg-sugar mixture.
Grease cookie sheet lightly.
Bake at 375° about ten minutes.
Do not let cookies brown.

title: gnome cookies
directions: Cook butter, egg, milk and sugar until thick.
Then add coconut, graham crackers and nuts.
Put a layer of graham crackers in bottom of pan or dish.
Put 1/2 of the above mixture on crackers, then another layer of crackers.
Put the rest of the mixture on crackers.

title: weight watchers banana split dessert
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed on package using skim milk.
Spread on crumbs.
Slice bananas on top of pudding.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Top with sliced strawberries (unsweetened) and crushed pineapple.

title: easy new york style cheesecake
directions: Blend ricotta and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, lemon juice, cornstarch, flour and butter.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
Fold in sour cream. Butter a 9-inch Spring pan.
Place in cold oven and turn to 325°. Bake for 1 hour then turn oven off.
Let cheesecake stand in oven for 2 hours.
When cheesecake is at room temperature (to the touch).
Top with a can of your favorite pie topping.
Spread gently as to not lift up any cheesecake.

title: christmas salad
directions: Make syrup of sugar, water and candies.
Place apples in the syrup when it begins to boil and remove them when liquid is clear red.
Don't turn apples too much or overcook.
Cool in refrigerator.
Combine the stuffing ingredients; add pecans and fill apples.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Place all in a buttered baking dish.
Spread part of the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp
directions: Dip shrimp into
beaten eggs and then into bread crumbs. Put garlic powder into bread crumbs first.
Then place into pan and stick sliced butter around the shrimp.
Cook for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine
sugar, syrup and water in 4 quart saucepan and boil until
it
spins a hair from the spoon.
Add raw peanuts. When peanuts
get
hot, they will pop and the husks will slide partially off.
Cook until the peanuts reach a golden color or however well
parched you like them.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and
soda.	Stir
quickly
and
pour
onto	a 13 x 9 x 1/2-inch
cookie
sheet
that has been greased with margarine. Let cool.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and cook cranberries, sugar and water until cranberries pop, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Best made 2 days before serving.

title: peach ice cream(makes 2 quarts)
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add milk.
Cook until thick, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Add peach pulp and lemon juice. Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze.

title: "vegetable sandwich spread"
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients. Stir over medium heat until gelatine dissolves; set aside. Cool.

title: chicken stew
directions: Use chicken broth from boiling chicken.
Add ingredients to broth and cook for 30 minutes.
Crumble crackers and add to pot to thicken.
Cook until well blended.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter; mix with peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over Rice Chex and mix.
Put powdered sugar into a large bag, put in cereal mixture and shake until coated.

title: seafood linguine
directions: Saute onion, garlic, green scallions in olive oil.
Add parsley and clam juice; simmer about 10 minutes.
Add clams, crab meat and remaining seafood and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
In another pot, bring water to a boil.
Add pasta and cook according to directions on package.
Drain pasta; add seafood mixture and mix. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients
in bowl and stir until slightly mixed. Too much stirring makes a
flat
cake!
Fry and serve.
I add 1/2 cup or so Baker's bran, usually.
You can find a recipe for sour dough starter in the miscellaneous section.

title: fettucini
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Toss and mix together with all ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Remove crusts from 9 slices of bread and soak in 1/4 pound melted butter.
Add 3/4 pound grated cheese.
Add 1/2 teaspoon pepper, 1/2 teaspoon dry mustard, 3 egg yolks and 2 cups of milk. Beat 3 egg whites and mold into mixture.
Pour into buttered baking dish and refrigerate overnight or at least 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: wilderness apple pie filling
directions: Cook until apples are tender; pack in sterile jars and seal. For pie, pour in crust and bake until crust is done.
Very good.

title: eggplant
directions: Use quantities as needed.

title: enchiladas
directions: Melt shortening in a small frypan.
Warm chile sauce mixture in another frypan.
Dip corn tortillas in shortening for 20 seconds or so and dip into chile sauce mixture.
Then place on cookie sheet open.
Fill with onion, cheese and two olives and roll.
Repeat for all 12 tortillas.
Sprinkle leftover cheese on top and olives, too.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: microwave pie filling
directions: Mix
together
until
egg yolks are mixed well.
Cook 2 minutes on	High
in microwave.
Stir and cook 2 more minutes. Stir and
cook
more minutes.
If you want it thicker, cook one more minute.

title: "pink pudding" cheesecake
directions: Mix graham crackers, powdered sugar, and melted butter.
Line bottom of 9x13 baking dish with half of mixture, and save rest for top.
Dissolve jello in 1 c. hot water.
Whip large can of Milnot until stiff.
When jello is cooled, pour into whipped Milnot. Cream together cream cheese and 1 c. sugar.
Add to jello/Milnot mixture, and blend.
Pour into graham cracker lined dish.
Top with remaining graham cracker mixture.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Cook sausage in skillet, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Break up sausage as it cooks.
Drain off fat.
Let cool.
In 2-quart bowl, mix meat, cheese, Bisquick and water; roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° on lightly greased cookie sheet until fluffed and browned. Serve hot.
Makes approximately 30 balls.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stir corn meal in boiling water.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and fat.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: onion casserole (sarah's way)
directions: Mix together the 2 cans of mushroom soup and milk.
In a 9 x 12-inch buttered casserole dish, alternate layers of thinly sliced onions, crushed chips and grated cheese.
Pour soup and milk mixture on top of onions, cheese and chip mixture; sprinkle with pepper.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Fill dish very full as it shrinks during cooking.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage head until leaves are soft.
Mix together meat, onion and eggs.
Spoon mixture into leaves and roll up using toothpicks when necessary.
Line bottom of pan with cabbage leaves and sauerkraut.
Make one layer of cabbage rolls.

Pour over rolls the tomatoes, tomato sauce and sauerkraut, then another layer of cabbage rolls, tomatoes, tomato sauce and remaining sauerkraut. Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, then uncovered for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes approximately 30 rolls.

title: miniature cheese onion loaves
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease bread pans (2 small or 1 large). Cook green onions in butter; set aside.
In large bowl, mix flour with baking powder, mustard, cheese and salt.
Add onions, milk and eggs.
Stir until flour is moistened.
Pour into pans and bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Freezes well.
Preheat in a 375° oven to serve.

title: shrimp goulash
directions: Simmer shrimp in butter until tender.
Add celery, onion and pepper to shrimp and simmer until tender-crisp.
Add corn with juice, salt and pepper to taste, 1 tablespoon sugar (or more if needed) and stewed tomatoes.
Simmer until vegetables are cooked. Serve over cooked rice.

title: annie hall's butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With an electric mixer (even the hand held kind will do), cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla and mix well.
Sift flour and salt together and beat into butter mixture until well mixed.
Roll out on lightly floured surface until dough is 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake for 10 minutes, but do not brown.
Remove cookies while still warm and cool on sheets of waxed paper.
Decorate if you like.

title: fruit dip
directions: Stir well and serve with assorted fresh fruit, cut up.

title: shrimp butter spread
directions: Chop shrimp fine in blender.
Melt cream cheese and butter in microwave, just until you can mix smooth.
Add shrimp, garlic powder and onion powder and whisk until well blended.
Pour into shallow dish and chill.
Serve at room temperature on crackers or veggies.

title: feather-light matzo balls *
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Gradually stir in matzo meal and remaining ingredients.
Let stand 20 minutes in refrigerator.
With wet hands, form into small balls.
Gently drop into large pot of lightly boiling water.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Yields about 16 balls.

title: date balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and cool. Add 2 cups Rice Krispies (1/2 cup chopped pecans are optional). Mix well. Shape into balls and dip into powdered sugar. Keep in a tin can.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In baking dish, layer cracker crumbs, asparagus, boiled eggs and cheese.
Continue in this manner until dish is almost full. Make 3 to 4 cups white sauce.
Add remaining cheese to sauce until melted.
Pour over casserole ingredients using knife to allow sauce to penetrate through.
Cover and bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles. Cut pickles into small slices and place in bowl. Add garlic, cut up real fine. Add some sugar and toss until sugar is partially dissolved. Place back into jar and fill completely with more sugar. Place in refrigerator. Shake pickles every once in awhile so that sugar will dissolve completely and will mix. Really good with cheese!!

title: worlds best banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a saucepan. Separate eggs. Stir yolks with a fork till blended. Put pan on low heat and allow to cook till custard forms and thickens. Stir often. Remove from heat, add butter and allow to melt. Cool. Add vanilla. Stir a couple times while it cools. Line a pyrex 9 x 5 1/2 x 2 1/2 inch pan with 3 layers of vanilla wafers and 3 layered of bananas. Pour cool custard over wafers and bananas. Add a couple sprinkles of cream or tartar to egg whites. With electric mixer, beat till frothy. Continue beating and add 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 tsp. vanilla. Spread on top. Bake at 375° in pre-heated oven till brown, 10-15 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook hen until tender.
Use 2 quarts of the broth for dropping dumplings.
Use 1 1/2 cups more broth for mixing with flour to make a thick dough.
Add 2 eggs to 1 1/2 cups broth.
Mix and add flour to make stiff dough.
Roll thin and drop in boiling broth. Cover and cook about 20 minutes on low heat.

title: chunky apple and raisin sauce for ham
directions: Cook apple wedges in butter in a large skillet over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine apple juice, brown sugar, raisins, lemon juice, cornstarch, ginger, mustard and cinnamon. Add to apples. Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes or until sauce is thickened. Serve sauce with ham.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Add carrots and stir until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Serve cold as a salad or warm as side dish.
Store in refrigerator up to two weeks.
Makes 8 cups.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Soak beans in 8 cups water overnight.
Next day, cook until tender with chopped onions.
Add other vegetables and cook.
Take out part of the beans and vegetables and blend.
Add back to soup; heat and serve.

title: lo-fat waffles
directions: Beat eggs with fork until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into hot waffle iron.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until shortening is the size of peas.
Add buttermilk, stirring with fork until dry ingredients are moistened. (Dough will resemble cottage cheese and be sticky.)
Turn dough out onto a heavily-floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times. Roll dough to 3/4 inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2 inch round cutter.
Place on lightly-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Brush with butter.
Yeild:
10 biscuits.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Follow instructions on cookie dough for baking except bake in small tart pan lined with baking paper cups.
While cookies are baking, unwrap candy.
Immediately press 1 candy in the center of each cookie.
The cookies will be puffed and collapse around candy.
Let cool, then remove from pan.

title: chicken katsu
directions: Slice open thick portions of chicken and make as flat as possible so that it will cook quickly.
Salt moderately and let stand at least 1 hour in refrigerator.
Put flour, eggs and panko flakes in three bowls.
Dip chicken in flour, then eggs and finally panko flakes.
(Be generous with flakes for crispy outer coating.) Fry until well done and golden brown in about 1/4-inch of oil. Drain on paper towels.
Slice into bite size pieces and serve with bottled Tonkatsu sauce.

title: five minute potage
directions: In a small saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add the garlic and onion.
Cook for 3 minutes, reduce heat and add the undiluted bean and bacon soup.
Stir to mix well, then add the can of stewed tomatoes, wine and Italian seasonings.
Mix well and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve with tossed green salad and crusty French bread.
Serves 2.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl; mix well. Alternate layers of chicken, broccoli and soup mixture in casserole until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds. Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until heated through.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: stump hole cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, 1 egg and pecans.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and spread with hands all over pan.
Beat sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: twinkle cake or suzy q's
directions: Cook the milk and flour until thick; cool. Add to this mixture the sugar and vanilla; beat 5 minutes. Beat Crisco and oleo 5 minutes. Divide mix and bake in two 9 x 13 pans for half of time or until done. Cool. Spread between layers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; cool. Add soup and cheese to mixture. Place in casserole dish and place in oven, baking for 30 minutes at 325°. Sprinkle dressing on top; return to oven and brown dressing.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: In skillet brown meat and drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn and tomato sauce.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
In a separate bowl prepare muffin mix according to package directions. Add 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spoon corn muffin mixture around outer edge of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes. Top corn bread with cheese; add remaining onions, baking 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix corn, onion, peppers and cabbage.
Pour into saucepan. Add seasonings, sugar and vinegar.
Cook slowly for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Pour in containers and seal.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Partially cook sliced potatoes, put in greased roasting pan. Salt, pepper, butter and grate some sharp cheese over potatoes.
In a saucepan, make a sauce of milk, salt, pepper and butter, thickened slightly with cornstarch.
Pour 3/4 sauce over potatoes. Put cooked ham slices over top.
Grate a small amount of sharp cheese over ham with the rest of the sauce.
Cook about 1/2 hour in 350° oven (uncovered) until slightly browned.

title: orange jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Strain fruit and add remaining liquid to equal 4 cups.
(Add orange juice if additional liquid needed.)
Slowly dissolve sherbet into mix.
Cut orange sections in half.
Mix fruit.
Put into sifter (very large) to finish chilling.
Decorate top with kiwi slices and mandarin oranges.

title: swedish nut rolls
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients as for pie dough. Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar. Add to warmed milk and add to dry ingredients. Add egg and blend. Let rise until doubled in bulk. Divide into 4 equal parts.
Roll each part into 10-inch circle on floured board. Brush with melted butter. Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nut mixture.
Cut circle into 16 wedges and roll from wide end to point. Allow to rise for 30 minutes. Bake 15 minutes on ungreased sheet at 350° until light brown.
Ice with confectioners icing.
Makes 64 rolls.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown ground beef slowly in little hot fat in heavy kettle. Add onions and cook 5 minutes more.
Add remaining ingredients except tomatoes and mix thoroughly, loosening the brown crustiness from bottom of kettle.
Bring to boil; cover, then simmer 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and if necessary, more water; simmer 10 minutes longer.
Makes 2 generous servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef; add onion, tomatoes, ketchup, steak sauce and parsley.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions and drain.
Combine noodles and beef mixtures; add soup and mix lightly.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Mix together and add 5 smashed bananas.
Prepare the day before.
Put in freezer and stir every 2 hours so it does not get icy.

title: gail's pie
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff.
Fold in sugar gradually, then add other ingredients.
Mix baking powder with cracker crumbs. Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes in large pie pan.
When cool, top with whipping cream and let stand in refrigerator not less than 8 hours.

title: 1-2-3 peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat peanut butter, water, butter, eggs and about half of the cake mix until smooth.
Add remaining cake mix; blend thoroughly.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough about 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Allow to cool a minute or two before removing from baking sheet.
May add chocolate chips.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Soften butter.
Mix butter, flour, sugar and vanilla together, then last add the pecans.
Take a spoon size amount and roll into a ball.
Put in the oven at 300° for 45 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Let cool completely, then roll in powdered sugar.
Great at Christmas time!!!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg.
Add peanut butter and dry ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Crisscross with wet fork. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and dry gelatin powder in heated fruit juice. Mix canned milk and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Add drained fruit and freeze.
(Good to freeze in 16 ounce can.)
Slice to serve.
Serve on lettuce, alone or with pumpkin, banana or date nut bread.
Spread with cream cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Dice ham
and
mix
all ingredients.
Mix and form into ball. Roll ball in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken and ham roulades
directions: Cook asparagus for roulade and for side dish separately.
For roulades, steam asparagus for 1 minute over boiling water, then plunge into cold water.
Drain thoroughly.
Repeat for asparagus as side dish, about 10 minutes, until crisp-tender.

title: pig lickin cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, oil, sugar, eggs and mandarin oranges together.
Pour into 3 round cake pans.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute celery and onion.
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish (or 2 smaller dishes).
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: glorified rice
directions: Cook rice in water.
Add a little salt.
Run cold water through rice and drain.
Mix rice, marshmallows and pineapple.
Add a little juice.
Let stand awhile.
Beat cream and add sugar to taste.
Add cream to rice mixture.
Chill.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Mix pie filling, pineapple, pecans and condensed milk together.
Add Cool Whip; fold in.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish. Chill for 3 hours.

title: master mix biscuits
directions: Add liquid to the mix all at once, stirring 25 strokes.
Knead 15 strokes on lightly floured board.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut. Bake on baking sheet in a hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Yield: 18 two-inch biscuits.

title: mystery pie
directions: Combine sugar, baking powder and vanilla with beaten egg whites.
Fold in chopped pecans and crumbled Ritz crackers.
Pour into ungreased glass pie dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown and drain sausage.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: starlight cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix sugar, eggs, shortening and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add flour and milk alternately, mixing until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake for about 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: the world's best chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift sugar and flour together. Dissolve soda in 1 cup hot water.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix with mixer 2 minutes until smooth.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Frost cake with any icing.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onions, pepper, celery and parsley in oil or bacon fat about 5 minutes.
Stir flour into vegetables, add tomatoes cut up. Cook about 5 minutes.
Add garlic, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir into mixture.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook about 5 minutes.

title: hot dog appetizers
directions: In saucepan, add red wine, brown sugar, ketchup and honey. Heat until hot and smooth.
Add hot dogs and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve with toothpicks.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook the sugar, corn syrup and butter over medium heat until soft ball stage, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and cream of tartar (will get foamy).
Drizzle syrup over popcorn, stirring to coat each kernel.
Put in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring often.
Store in airtight container.

title: homemade mac 'n cheese
directions: Place cooked noodles into deep baking dish; add mushroom soup and both cheeses.
Mix thoroughly.
Top with a thin layer of bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° until a layer of crust forms on top, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: gumdrop squares
directions: Mix the applesauce, the unflavored gelatin, the fruit flavored gelatin, sugar and lemon juice; heat to boiling and boil 1 minute, stirring frequently.
Fill loaf pan halfway to the top with cold water.
Pour out the water, then immediately pour the gelatin mixture into the wet pan, using rubber scraper to clean the side of the saucepan.
When the loaf pan is cool enough to touch, refrigerate about 3 hours or until candy is firm.
Cut the candy into 1 inch squares (dip the knife in a glass of water to keep the candy from sticking).
Lift each square from the pan onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Let stand at least 8 hours to dry. After candy has dried, place some sugar in bowl, then roll each square in the sugar until all sides are coated.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°; reduce heat to 350° and bake 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: great chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Put other ingredients in crock-pot.
Add meat and cook.
Serve over regular size corn chips and salad.

title: chicken asparagus casserole(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Combine chicken, mushroom soup and almonds.

Pat in 13 x 9 baking dish. Combine asparagus and pimento; put over chicken mixture. Cover and bake in 350° oven 60 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle onions around edge. Bake 5 minutes longer or until heated through.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls (1-inch).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in boiling salt water until tender and then drain.
Mash until very smooth.
Add remaining ingredients except for cheese and beat until light and fluffy.
Cool.
Cover and place in refrigerator (may store for two weeks).
To use, place in greased dishes; dot with butter and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through, about 1 hour.
To double recipe, double all ingredients except for cream cheese (use one 8 ounce).
Put in 6-quart casserole.
Wonderful, as you can make it ahead of time and it serves a lot of company!

title: margaret's molded salad
directions: Make jello per recipe. Add rest of ingredients. Serve plain for side dish. Top with whip topping for dessert.

title: pear ginger tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 10-inch quiche dish with Pam. Pare and slice pears.
In blender, place milk, sugar, egg whites, yolk, ginger, vanilla, salt and flour.
Blend.
Arrange pears in a dish.
Pour batter over them.
Top with almonds.
Bake 1 hour or until knife comes clean.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cooled.

title: outdoorsman's bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Melt butter, pour over top of bread in pan.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes or until brown.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans and press into pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Prepare German chocolate cake according to directions.
Pour over first mixture.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and margarine and spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers and onions with salt.
Let stand 10 minutes. Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to cucumbers.

title: turkey wild rice soup
directions: Crumble ground turkey into 6-quart saucepan or Dutch oven. Stir in onion and carrots.
Cook over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth, rice, poultry seasoning, pepper and thyme.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 to 55 minutes or until tender.
Place flour in a small bowl. Gradually add milk, blending until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until soup bubbles and thickens slightly.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; mix well.
Put in small pie plate and freeze.
Makes
16 servings, divided evenly, each equals 1 serving fruit.

title: diet apple bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: e. t. fingers
directions: Melt morsels over double boiler.
Beat until creamy.
Mix in noodles and nuts (seems dry, but keep mixing).
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Makes 60.
Will harden in 15 minutes or more.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix and bake 1/2 hour in 350° oven.

title: crock-pot french dip sandwiches
directions: Place in crock-pot all day.
Slice or shred beef.
Put on hoagie buns. Add 2 cups water to juice to dilute for dipping sandwich.

title: almond poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl of mixer, combine sugar, oil, eggs, almond, vanilla and butter extract.
Beat to blend. Combine and sift flour, poppy seed, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Begin and end with dry ingredients.
Mix to blend.
Spray muffin pan with Pam or use 2 1/2-inch bake cups.
Bake muffins 30 minutes at 350°. Makes 24 muffins.

title: lasagna
directions: In large pan brown beef and onion in oil, drain fat and add sauce and spices.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cool lasagna and drain.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread 1 cup sauce.
Alternate layers of lasagna, Ricotta, sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese, ending with sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: seafoam candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan combine sugar, syrup and vinegar.
Bring to the boil over high heat.
Reduce to low heat and cook slowly until temperature reaches 300°.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda while stirring.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool. Break into small pieces.
Melt chocolate chips with shortening. Dip candy pieces in chocolate mixture.

title: tomato jam
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut up.
Add sugar.
Boil for 10 minutes. Mash with potato masher while boiling.
When done, remove from heat and add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Put in containers and put in freezer.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for several hours before serving.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart saucepan.
Add rice and onion. Brown, but do not burn.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring frequently, until rice kernels are soft.
Add water by small amounts if needed.
Serve as an accompaniment to chicken, beef or pork roast.

title: creamy yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Add soup, sour cream, peppers (or) pimentos, water chestnuts and onions.
Set aside 1/3 of margarine. Melt the other 2/3 margarine and mix with stuffing mix.
Use half stuffing mix to line bottom of 2-quart baking dish, then cover with squash mixture.
Top with rest of stuffing mix and dot with the rest of the margarine that was set aside.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scandinavian meatballs
directions: Combine ground turkey mix and dill weed in large bowl until blended.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown meatballs in the butter or margarine, part at a time.
Transfer meatballs into casserole dish.
Sprinkle flour over the pan drippings and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture bubbles.
Stir in milk, water and instant chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Stir in 2 tablespoons dill weed.
Pour sauce over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: skillet chicken paella
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook chicken strips in hot oil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add onion and garlic to skillet; cook until tender, but not brown.
Remove skillet from heat.
Add broth, uncooked rice, oregano, paprika, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, about 15 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes, sweet peppers and frozen peas to skillet.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked chicken.
Cook and stir 1 minute more or until heated through.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine.
Sprinkle corn flakes over margarine.
Add cooked cabbage and grated cheese over top.
Blend together mayonnaise, soup and milk in saucepan until thick.
Pour over the first layer.
Sprinkle few corn flakes over all ingredients in pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fabulous bran muffins
directions: Mix oil, sugar, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add buttermilk alternately with Raisin Bran.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Mixture keeps 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Add scalded milk, cooked rice and drained raisins. Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes or until knife comes clean.

title: oatmeal rounds
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients, then oatmeal and nuts.
Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet at 325° for about 15 minutes.

title: diane's pear pie
directions: Put 1/2 of Cool Whip in a bowl.
Stir in sour cream, pears and cheese.
Pour into pie shell and top with rest of Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: roast pheasant
directions: Soak pheasant overnight in salt water.	Next day season pheasant
with
salt,
Accent
and pepper by hand rubbing into flesh.
Tie
legs
together.
Heat	14-inch Dutch oven with 16 coals on
top
and 14 coals on the bottom for 10 minutes; then lower heat	(leaving
coals
on
top
and
10 coals on the bottom).
Cover
breast
with
bacon slices and roast, basting occasionally with
oil to keep bird from drying out.
Roast 15 minutes per pound.

title: grandma annie's blonde brownies
directions: Put dry ingredients and nuts in bowl.
Melt margarine and add brown sugar.
Mix well.
Cool.
Add eggs and mix well; add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: scalloped scallops
directions: Cut scallops into bite size pieces and cover bottom of casserole with one layer.
Sprinkle pepper on scallops and then pats of butter.
Crumble crackers in hand.
Keep layering, ending with crackers.
Pour light cream and mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash almost completely. Cook onion and mix in soup and sour cream.
Add dressing mix with seasoning, then add to melted butter.
Place 1/2 of dressing in casserole dish, placing rest of ingredients in, except cheese.
Put rest of dressing mix on, then grated cheese.

title: peanut butter meltaway cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan over low heat until it bubbles (not boiling).
Take off heat and add next 4 ingredients. Beat until smooth; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix peanut butter and oil. Spread over cooled cake.
Place in refrigerator for at least 20 minutes.

title: granola(low-cal)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine oil, syrup, honey and vanilla. Add to oat mixture and toss to combine.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick coating and spread oat mixture.
Bake, stirring frequently, until lightly browned for 8 to 10 minutes. Watch carefully. Transfer cookie sheet to wire rack and let cool. Transfer oat mixture to a medium mixing bowl.
Add dried fruit and toss to combine.
Store in airtight container for up to one week.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix
first
ingredients well and add the vanilla and real lemon juice.
Next add flour,
milk
and
cocoa,
mixing well. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt in saucepan and bring to a boil the margarine, shortening, cocoa and water.
Blend and add the sugar, salt, flour and soda. Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in an oblong cake pan. Five minutes before cake is done; mix topping.

title: butter herb baked fish
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix crushed saltines, Parmesan, herbs, salt and garlic powder in bowl.
Dip fish fillets in butter, then in saltine mixture.
Place in butter in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Brown under broiler a few minutes to crisp crust.

title: steamed vegetables
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, heat broth and vegetables to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Drain.

title: old fashion no fail recipe
directions: Very lightly beat the first 8 ingredients in a bowl of love. Moisten with tears of heartfelt sympathy.
Bake in a good natured pan.
Sprinkle with prayer, then add icing.
Serve repeatedly.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Next a.m. wash beans thoroughly.
Cover with water.
Chop up onion and add to beans.
Let boil.
Add baking soda, turn heat down and simmer.
Add other ingredients. Cut salt pork in small pieces and add to all the ingredients. Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: lime marinated fish steaks
directions: For marinade, combine first 5 ingredients in jar; cover and shake vigorously.
Pour over fish steaks; marinate 15 minutes, turning once.
Remove fish from marinade.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat source, about 5 to 6 minutes per side or until fish is opaque and flakes easily with fork.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, nutmeg and flour thoroughly in bowl.
Add peaches with juice and lemon juice to sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Place one pie crust in bottom of pan; press to sides and corners. Prick crust with fork along bottom and sides.
Pour peach mixture into pan.
