Cut butter on top of mixture.
Place second crust on top of pan.
Press to corners and sides.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until cobbler is browned.

title: cheese nachos(microwave dish)
directions: Arrange chips on two 9-inch micro-type serving platters.
Cover each with cheese, chilies and olives.
Cook one plate at a time, 4 to 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: easy chocolate delight pie
directions: Melt all but 3 squares of chocolate with 1/4 cup milk.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Melt remaining chocolate and drizzle over pie.

title: potato rolls
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle yeast into warm water.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in butter, shortening, sugar and potatoes, then cold water and enough flour to make dough stiff.
Place dough in large, greased clean bowl.
Brush top with vegetable oil; cover tightly with waxed paper or foil, then with a clean towel. Refrigerate.

title: icebox pickled okra(8 servings)
directions: In 5-cup glass container with tight-fitting lid, combine okra and salt. In saucepan over high heat, bring vinegar to a rolling boil; pour over okra. Keep okra submerged in vinegar with a small saucer or plate. Cover with vented plastic wrap and let cool to room temperature; cover and chill 24 hours.

title: bite size pizzas
directions: Pull each biscuit into four or five pieces and place on cookie sheet.
Spread pizza sauce over each.
Place pepperoni slice, hamburger or other choices on each.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Lightly mix beef, rice, onions and seasonings.
Shape into 12 meatballs.
Brown in hot oil.
Pour on tomato sauce and water. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato royal
directions: Cook sweet potatoes, drain and mash. Combine first five ingredients and

spoon into a buttered casserole dish. Bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with coconut. Arrange marshmallows on top and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: easy kid's punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine 7-Up and Hi-C.
Spoon sherbet into little scoops and float on top.

title: frosted pretzels
directions: Place frosting in a 2-cup glass measure; microwave at High 30 to 45 seconds or until frosting melts, stirring once.
Dip half of each pretzel into frosting, allowing excess to drip.
Place on wax paper.
Let dry 2 hours or until no longer sticky.
Serve same day.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: skillet spinach
directions: In skillet saute onion in margarine.
Add spinach.
Sprinkle sugar and salt.
Cover and cook over medium heat until spinach is wilted and tender, about 5 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: party chicken
directions: (If you like lots of sauce, you can double the cream of chicken with sour cream mixture.)

title: apricot champagne punch
directions: Blend ingredients in blender and freeze. Scoop out with ice cream scoop; place in champagne glass and pour champagne over it.

title: rye bread or rolls
directions: Combine flours.
Stir 1 1/2 cups flour mix, 1 1/2 teaspoon caraway seed and next 3 ingredients.
Combine milk, 1 cup water and oleo in saucepan.
Lower heat until very warm (120° to 130°). Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, for 2 minutes.
Add 3/4 cup flour mix.
Beat at high speed.
Stir in enough flour to make dough stiff.
Cover and raise for 40 minutes.
Stir down and turn into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Brush lightly with oil and sprinkle with caraway.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn out of pan to cool.

title: lemon-parsleyed potatoes
directions: Wash and slice potatoes.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Place in a serving bowl and keep warm.
Melt butter.
Stir in parsley and lemon juice.
Pour over potatoes; stir lightly to coat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: butternut-apple crisp
directions: Combine all ingredients; turn into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cover with foil.

title: amy smith's angel pecan pie
directions: Mix beaten eggs and add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff and gradually add sugar, then fold in pecans, wafers or Ritz and vanilla.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Put in preheated oven at 325° for 35 minutes.
Take out and cool.
Mix 1/2 pint whipping cream and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Put on top of pie.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top of pie.

title: spray cleaner
directions: Pour into a quart jar and stir.
Pour into a spray bottle and use as a window cleaner.
Cleans greasy scum around stove.
It's also great on dirty woodwork.

title: fritters
directions: Let stand 1 hour, then drop spoonfuls into hot grease.
Serve hot with butter and syrup.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Layer the chicken, tomatoes, soups, broth and tortillas in a greased 2-quart disposable casserole. Add chopped onions. Repeat layers and onions. Sprinkle grated cheese over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg, milk, vanilla. Sift flour. Add to cream mixture. Chill. Cut and bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: barbecue potato chip chicken
directions: Clean
chicken	breast,
taking
off the skin. Dip each piece in	melted	stick
margarine and roll in crushed chips. Pour
some melted margarine in baking dish and place chicken. Top
each piece
with
melted
margarine and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix the apples, sugar, 1 tablespoon flour, cinnamon and lemon juice; put in unbaked pie crust.
Cover with the melted margarine, 1/2 cup flour and brown sugar.
Top with second crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: concord grape pie
directions: Slip skins from grapes and set aside.
Bring pulp to boil. Reduce heat and simmer until mushy.
Press pulp through colander to rid seeds.
Add skins back to pulp and mix together.
Add sugar, flour, lemon juice and salt and mix.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves together. In a separate bowl, cream sugar and shortening together until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the applesauce, beating it very well after each addition.
Combine raisins, pecans, walnuts and 1 tablespoon flour.
Stir into the butter slowly.
Pour batter into a 9-inch greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until cake springs back when pressed.
Cool, then serve.

title: lynn's foolproof stuffing for thanksgiving turkey
directions: In a large skillet, crumble sausage.
Cook and stir until sausage is brown.
Drain off all but 1/4 cup drippings.
Add butter, celery, onion and carrot.
Cook, stirring occasionally until onion is tender.
In a very large bowl, combine bread cubes, apple, sage, thyme, rosemary, parsley and sausage mixture.
Toss lightly.
Add enough broth to moisten.
Salt and pepper to taste. Use to stuff 1 (10 to 12 pound) turkey.

title: ice box cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients by hand to make sure there are no clumps of raisins or cherries.
Cook marshmallows and milk over low heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows melt.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix until everything is moist.
Mix before mixture gets cool.
Pour into tube pan greased well with margarine.
Refrigerate.
Cake will keep several weeks in refrigerator and it may be frozen as well.

title: mama gay's eagle brand milk
directions: Combine boiling water and margarine and put in blender; process on low speed.
Add sugar and blend on low; add dry milk and blend until well mixed.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 cups, which tastes the same as commercial Eagle Brand milk.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a shortbread crust or graham cracker crust.
Chill until set.
Top with cherries or strawberries.

title: crushed pear salad
directions: Drain pears, reserving 1 1/2 cups of juice.
Mash pears with fork.
Heat juice to boiling, then add lime Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add softened cream cheese.
Stir in mashed pears. When all is cooled, add the Cool Whip.
Pour into a large mold and chill until set.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: In a saucepan, mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter, then spoon onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking power, cinnamon and pecans. (Set aside.)
Beat eggs lightly in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy; stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until moistened. Spoon batter into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Turn out on rack and cool.

title: cheesy cornbread
directions: Brown sausage and onions together in a skillet until done, about 10 minutes.
Mix other ingredients except cheese in a mixing bowl.

title: gingerbread - g'g'ma's
directions: Blend sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Stir in molasses.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk; beat well.
Spread in well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: black olive roll-ups
directions: Mix the black olives and cream cheese until spreadable. Spread on flour tortillas and roll up.
May be dipped in salsa or picante sauce.

title: penn-cumberland's sausage balls
directions: Work 1 lb. uncooked sausage into 4 cups biscuit mix, 1/2 lb. grated cheese, and 2 teaspoons crumbled sage.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: Cook the sugar, flour, salt, pineapple juice and egg over moderate heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Set aside to cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli slightly underdone.
Place in pan and pour soup over it.
Spread Cheez Whiz over; top with dressing spread over that.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, mushroom soup and minced onion.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with French fried onions and bake for 5 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: blackberry cheese pie
directions: Mix crumbs, margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: banana fruit salad with sauce
directions: Slice bananas and chunk apples.
Mix with pineapple chunks, pecans and marshmallows.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ice cream soda
directions: Put the syrup in a tall glass and add a splash of the sparkling water and stir well.
Add the ice cream.
Fill with sparkling water and stir well.
Serve with a long handled spoon and straw.
Serves 1.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Cream 3/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons butter and stir in milk. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons cocoa and add to creamed mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread in buttered 9-inch square pan.

title: venison sausage(20 patties)
directions: Cut meat in small pieces and mix well, with all ingredients. Put through a fine chopper twice.
Form into patties 1/2 inch thick.
Pan-fry or broil.

title: peach cobbler quickie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium size Pyrex dish, empty peaches (with juice).
Place pecans over peaches. Take cake mix from box and sprinkle over peaches and pecans.
Top with patties of margarine.
Cook in a 350° oven until golden brown (approximately) 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes a delicious dessert.
Can be made without pecans.

title: parisian onion soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add broth and pepper.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Pour soup into bowls.
Top with toast.
Cover with cheese; broil until melted.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: low-fat pasta by carl
directions: Steam broccoli in microwave.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add crushed or chopped tomatoes and add broccoli.
Stir and simmer.
Add broccoli and shells and simmer.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Combine water, vinegar, flour, sugar and eggs in top of double boiler. Cook until thickened and smooth, stirring often. Add butter and lemon flavoring. Pour into pie shell. To serve, top with whipped cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and stir. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Bake cake 15 to 20 minutes.
Use 1/2 sheet cake or 1-inch cookie sheet (deep).
Cook cake completely and leave in pan.
Prepare pudding with 1 cup milk.
Cool completely.
Soften cream cheese and add pudding.
Add Cool Whip last.
Sprinkle well with drained pineapple on top, then coconut and walnuts.

title: poppy seed cake or bread
directions: Mix thoroughly; pour into greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 2 regular size loaves or 1 Bundt cake. Sprinkle cake with powdered sugar while still warm.

title: crunchy romaine toss
directions: Brown walnuts and noodles in butter; cool on paper towels. Combine noodles and walnuts with broccoli, romaine and onions. Pour Sweet and Sour Dressing over and toss to coat well. Serves 10 to 12.

title: strawberry banana mold
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and pour 3/4 of this into jello mold.
Set 10 minutes or until jelled.
Spread the sour cream over the jello.
Then add rest of the jello.
Refrigerate at least 1 day.

title: reese's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together the flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually blend into butter mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
(Do not overbake. Cookies will be soft.
They will puff while baking and flatten while cooling.) Let cool and then remove from cookie sheet. Yields about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until soft enough to mash.
Add all ingredients except bread crumbs and 1 cup grated cheese.
Mix 1 cup cheese and bread crumbs together and sprinkle on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: poor man cake
directions: Cook all together, except flour and baking powder, until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Let cool.
Add flour and baking powder.
Bake in a large tube pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 cup pecans. Form into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Roll in 1 cup pecans.
Serve with crackers. They freeze well.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine
ingredients and stir well.
Pour in pie crusts and refrigerate
approximately
12 hours.
Makes 2 pies.
One sixth of a pie contains 523 calories.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into small or medium size pieces.
Pour oil over potatoes.
Sprinkle soup over potatoes and stir to coat well.
Put into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Mix brown sugar, water and vinegar.
Cook until syrup forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Pour syrup over beaten egg whites.
Beat continually until candy is stiff enough to hold its shape, then work in nuts and vanilla.
Drop with teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
and
drain broccoli.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix together
mushroom	soup, sour cream, cheese and onions.
Pour mixture
over broccoli.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers with melted margarine.	Place
on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until hot.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Beat all the ingredients together one at a time in the order they are listed.
When batter is creamy, pour into spring pan that has been lightly buttered and floured.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Bake 10 minutes at 500°, then 1 hour at 200°.
Let firm up before cutting.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix together all ingredients; roll mixture into balls, then roll in flour.
Flatten slightly with palm of hand.
Fry in corn oil; turn once or twice until brown.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Whip all ingredients until spreadable.

title: cheese soup
directions: Simmer 1 quart water, the chicken bouillon cubes, onion and chopped celery for 30 minutes.
Add the carrots, potatoes and mixed vegetables; simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir in the cream of chicken soup and diced cheese.
Cook until cheese is smooth.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Combine the white cake mix, 1 cup blackberry wine, blackberry jelly, canola oil and eggs. Mix on low until well blended. Grease Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Remove from oven.

title: barley pilaff
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in half of the butter.
When tender, place in casserole.
Cook barley in remaining butter over low heat, stirring constantly, until almond colored.
Add to ingredients in casserole and mix together.
Pour broth over all and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cover for first half of cooking time.

title: cream scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly butter a cookie sheet.
Mix the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt in a large bowl.

title: hot golden olive bites
directions: Stuff each pitted olive with the tiny cubes of Cheddar cheese. Combine biscuit mix, butter, milk and spices to form a dough. Mold a teaspoon of dough around each olive, covering it completely.
Place on baking sheet and bake in a preheated 400° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk.
Gradually add milk; stir thoroughly.
Pour into your favorite pie crust (9-inch deep). Bake about 1 hour or until done.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Mix jello and water together.
Add pineapple and strawberries. Pour half of mixture in mold; let congeal.
Spread sour cream on firm jello.
Pour remaining mixture over sour cream.
Return to refrigerator until set.
This is quick and easy to make and looks pretty too.

title: vegie dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate one hour.

title: chicken mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter and cook mushrooms.
Sprinkle in flour and salt; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Gradually whisk in cream, then broth.
Add chicken.
When hot add sherry and serve immediately.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: joshua's favorite brisket
directions: Rinse brisket in cold water.
Place in baking pan.
Sprinkle with kosher salt.
Slice carrots and onions (very thin).
Put on top of brisket.
In a separate bowl, add chili sauce, beer and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Pour mixture on top of brisket.
Seal pan with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 450°, then reduce to 350° for 2 hours. Keep covered the entire time.
This is a great company dish. Slice thinly and serve!!

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; add salt and pepper.
Chop cooked chicken into bite-size pieces.
Boil spaghetti in chicken stock; add water, if needed.
Saute onions and bell peppers in oleo.
Add to chicken and spaghetti.
Add tomatoes, cheese and all remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: quick apple turnovers
directions: Roll each biscuit into oval shape.
Place biscuits, one at a time, in 13 x 9-inch pan coated with Pam.
Place a small piece of apple on biscuit, flip top over and pinch edges down.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Melt sugar, butter and water.
Pour entire mixture over biscuits.
Bake in 350° oven until biscuits are done (approximately 15 minutes).

title: miniature cheesecake tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and smooth.
Line muffin tins with cupcake papers.
Place one vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cup.
Fill 2/3 cup full; bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
When cool, top with filling of choice (any pie filling; strawberry, cherry, etc.).
Serves 18 to 20.

title: tropical salad
directions: Drain oranges and fruit cocktail. Mix together in a bowl. Add Cool Whip and coconut; chill and serve.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, then mix with beans and seasoning. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan the sauce, shells, meat, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Repeat layer and top with sauce and Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable turkey casserole
directions: In a 3-quart baking dish, mix soup, milk and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and turkey.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until mixture begins to bubble.
Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into quarters.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Split breasts.
Remove bones and skin.
Rinse and dry.
Place margarine in skillet and brown breasts, salting lightly.
Lift breasts into greased roasting pan, not touching.
Mix juice and soy sauce; pour half over them.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Baste about every 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: eye of round roast
directions: Sear roast in Dutch oven in a small amount of oil.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over roast and add vinegar mixed with 2 cups of water.
Cook, covered, on top of stove at medium-low temperature until meat sticks tender.
To thicken gravy, use flour and water mixture; also add Kitchen Bouquet for color.
Carrots and potatoes can be added to last hour of cooking.

title: easy vegetable bake
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Mix melted margarine with crackers.
Mix celery, mayonnaise and cheese and stir into vegetables.
Pour into large baking dish.
Cover with cracker mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cathedral cookies
directions: You will need wax paper.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and spread on platter.
Next spread hot sauce over layer, then shredded Colby-Jack cheese, chopped tomatoes and chopped green olives.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: english berry pudding
directions: Line bottom and sides of bowl with closely-placed bread slices. Combine berries and preserves; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon 1/2 berry mix on bread.
Cover with half the remaining bread triangles and then rest of berry mixture. Layer on remaining bread.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Wash and cut broccoli into small pieces.
Place in medium saucepan; add next seven ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil; simmer until tender.
Remove some flowerets and set aside for garnish.
Puree or blend remaining broccoli.
Return to heat and stir in Milnot.
Heat to serving temperature.
This recipe can also be used with asparagus, mushrooms or zucchini.

title: quick 'n easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Mix hamburger, tomato sauce, onion, green pepper, garlic and mushrooms.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Cook noodles.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach soup
directions: Cook spinach for 4 minutes; drain.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add spinach, salt and pepper.
Saute over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Beat egg yolks with cheese; add to the spinach.
Gradually add broth, stirring constantly; bring to a boil.
(The eggs will curdle; don't worry.)
Serve with croutons.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes.
Peel and cube into small to medium size pieces.
Stir in onions.
Mix sour cream, cottage cheese and mayonnaise together.
Pour over potato mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Spread in 8 x 11-inch or 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over top.
Spoon melted margarine over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: marinated pepper and herb chicken
directions: In small saucepan, combine all ingredients, except chicken. Heat until bouillon dissolves.
Cool.
Pour over chicken. Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Remove chicken from marinade and grill, broil or microwave as desired, basting frequently with marinade.
Serves 6.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients. Use 3 tablespoons to each cup of hot water.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Adding pecans last, pour into pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes and reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer or until a knife inserted in center of filling comes out clean.

title: smoked, glazed chicken
directions: Grill over charcoal until done, then place in a covered grill or smoker and smoke with hickory chips for 30 to 45 minutes.
Brush with the following glaze and place over coals again.
Repeat this glazing several times.

title: cream cheese frosting for carrot cake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add milk until desired consistency is reached.

title: bananas amaretto
directions: Peel and slice bananas into uniformly sized coins; place in casserole dish.
Melt margarine in a small uncovered bowl in microwave on High for 45 to 55 seconds.
Stir in lemon juice, brown sugar and Amaretto.
Microwave the mixture, uncovered, on High for 40 to 50 seconds or until hot.
Stir mixture and pour over bananas, tossing gently.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 minute or until hot.
Do not overheat or bananas will turn mushy. Divide into individual serving dishes and drizzle with sauce. Serves 4.

title: deviled chicken wings
directions: Cut off and discard tips of wings.
Cut each wing in half at the joint.
Sprinkle with salt.
Combine honey, mustard, lemon juice and ginger.
Mix well.
Marinate wings several hours or overnight.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Baste occasionally with marinade.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: oven-scrambled eggs
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt and scalded milk; mix.
Pour into melted butter and bake 15 minutes.
Stir; bake approximately another 15 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: pimento cheese spread(for sandwiches or crackers)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put enough mayonnaise to right consistency to spread.
(Taste to see if sweet enough or salted enough.)

title: cream of potato soup
directions: In a large pot, cook potatoes, celery and onion in just enough water to cover them.
Cook about 10 minutes, until tender.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, celery, carrots and salt in water.
Boil until done.
Add butter, flour and pepper.
Cook until thick.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Freezes well.

title: pasties
directions: Preheat oven to 325° (350° at lower altitudes).
Combine ground meat, potatoes, onion, carrot and spices in large mixing bowl.
Set aside.

title: roast with carrots, potatoes, onions and cabbage
directions: *Season to your taste.

title: cranberry-pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together in a large bowl all dry ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into dry mixture only until moistened.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans that have been greased.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until bread tests done with wooden pick.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove to cooling rack.

title: chicken-sausage casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts; cut up in bite size pieces.
Brown sausage; drain.
Cook rice according to package directions. Combine first 5 ingredients.
Bake at 350° in casserole dish for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven.
Top with onions; return to oven until brown, 5 or 10 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store, covered, in refrigerator up to 8 weeks.
Bake in muffin tin at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pluto pie
directions: Line skillet with foil in 9-inch or 10-inch skillet.
Spread with tomato sauce, cheese, oregano and parsley.
Spread bread crumbs and meat over.
Cover skillet and cook over flame for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add all other ingredients with 3 cups water.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand 5 minutes.
Combine yeast mixture, butter and flour in large bowl, mixing well.
Stir in egg and sugar.
(Mixture will be a very soft batter.)
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, garlic juice, cornflakes, onion, eggs, salt and pepper together and make small meatballs.
Mix jelly, chili sauce and lemon juice in skillet and simmer 5 minutes.
Drop meatballs in sauce and cook 45 minutes on medium heat.
You may leave meatballs in or take them out of skillet, but if left in, skim grease off meatballs.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Stir constantly until heated.
Pour over pickles.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: fruit-nut bars
directions: Mix and sift first four ingredients.
Make a well in mixture and add in order, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add dates, nuts and coconut.
Turn into greased shallow baking dish (12 x 7 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm and remove from pan when cooled.

title: cranberry vodka punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice cocktail and vodka in a large punch bowl.
Set a block of ice or mold in the center.
Add ginger ale and club soda; stir in gently to blend. Garnish with pineapple chunks.
Makes about 5 quarts or 40 (4 ounce) servings.

title: knorr vegetable dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature. Drain water chestnuts and pimentos. Mix all ingredients until well blended. This dip is good with chips, crackers or vegetable sticks. Good for parties.

title: nancy clancy's red clam sauce(yield:  4 servings)
directions: 1. Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients, one at a time, mixing well with each addition.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: caesar-style salad
directions: Wash lettuce; tear into bite-size pieces.
Combine with walnuts, cheese and dressing to taste.
Toss to blend.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: ground beef special(sloppy joes)
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: This is so easy to make and people will just hover over the dish.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and rinse.
Combine soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Add macaroni and mix well.
Add enough extra milk to come to top of mixture in casserole dish.
Cover top with bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Beat until fluffy.
Gradually add Eagle Brand milk, stirring until well mixed.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Turn into prepared crust and chill two to three hours, then garnish with cherry filling.

title: icebox muffins
directions: Pour hot water over 40% bran flakes and let stand.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk and 40% bran flakes. Mix flour, soda, salt and all-bran.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir until all is moistened.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 1 gallon or 5 to 6 dozen.
Keeps 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.
Dough may be frozen unbaked.

title: tuna spring salad
directions: Mix olives, carrot, celery, parsley, onion and vinegar.
Mix cottage cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Break tuna into large flakes with fork.
Add vegetable and cheese mixtures.
Toss lightly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: golden brown oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Dip chicken in sour cream mix.
Dredge in stuffing mix.
Place chicken in baking dish. Drizzle with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel food cake delight
directions: Cut up the angel food cake into cubes.
Add the cool whip, prepared pudding and strawberries.
Stir well and chill until time to eat.
Very light and good.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice onions into several rings.
Mix all other ingredients together to make batter.
Dip the onions into the batter and deep fry until golden brown.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir peanut butter, sugar and eggs in a bowl until blended (mixture will be sticky).
With floured hands, roll level tablespoon into balls 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine caramels, Eagle Brand milk and margarine in a bowl and melt together in microwave oven.
Stir often.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown meat in large skillet over medium heat; drain off fat. Add water and vegetables.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover tightly.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in microwave.
Add Bisquick and sausage.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° on lightly greased cookie sheet until brown, about 15 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° in three 8-inch layer pans for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hobos
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread in hot dog bun and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: watergate congealed salad
directions: Mix pudding, pineapple with juice, nuts and marshmallows together.
Fold in Cool Whip topping.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
In medium mixing bowl, blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well with a spoon.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in oleo.
Drain.
Add garlic juice.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add sauce, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: pear jello salad
directions: Drain pears.
Heat pear juice and pour over jello.
Stir in cream cheese mashed with milk.
Cool in refrigerator, but do not let set.
When cool, add pears which have been blended.
Add Cool Whip.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours, or until set.

title: carrot-squash bake
directions: In a saucepan, cook squash or zucchini and onion in 2 cups boiling water and 1/2 teaspoon salt, uncovered, for 5 minutes; stir once.
Drain.
In a bowl, combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in squash mixture.
Combine stuffing mix and butter or margarine.
Sprinkle 2/3 of the stuffing mixture in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture atop.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture around edges of dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: butter dips
directions: Mix well and roll out onto floured board, about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into strips and put into buttered pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon together.
Let stand overnight.
Add bacon just before serving.

title: banana split
directions: Crumble graham crackers; mix with 8 tablespoons melted butter. Press into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Combine soft margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla and rum; pour mixture onto graham crackers. Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Split bananas and place on top of mixture. Drain pineapple and spread on top of bananas.
Next, spread Cool Whip.
Top with nuts, cherries and chocolate chips.
Refrigerate.

title: blushing fruit elegant
directions: Measure juice from fruit and add water to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Combine with Jell-O, spices, lemon juice and food coloring.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until Jell-O dissolves.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add brandy.
Arrange fruit in a glass shallow 2-quart baking dish. Pour mixture over fruit and chill.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: salmon soup
directions: Saute peppers and onion in butter.
Add and cook celery soup, milk, canned tomatoes, potatoes and carrots.
Drain and clean salmon; add last.
